research/history/round_summaries/round_0060.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Round 59 ruled out `factorized_topk` as a strong matched alternative under the current `gated` recipe: at `0.229180` it was clearly too weak, so the next single architecture question should move to a different export-compatible support-formation mechanism rather than another heavier scoring path. `jumprelu` preserves LUTurbo's static-vector finite weighted-sum reconstruction contract while replacing the learned input-conditioned gate with per-latent thresholding, so this round asks one clean yes/no question: under the exact current mainline recipe (`K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`), is `jumprelu` competitive enough in full-curve behavior to justify any later follow-up as a potentially cheaper deployment family?",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0060.json:20:    "summary": "Run one matched architecture probe on `jumprelu`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and the same runtime knobs, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `jumprelu`. Judge this probe by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `jumprelu` stays smooth and remains reasonably close to the `0.142923` `gated` anchor, it is worth keeping in reserve because its thresholded support path may reduce LUTurbo online selection overhead versus a full gating branch; if it is clearly worse across the curve, archive it as a non-promising matched alternative and return to the `gated` mainline next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0060.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0060.json:79:      "Round 59 showed that matched `factorized_topk` is not promising under the strengthened mainline recipe: its `0.229180` endpoint is far from the `gated@128` anchor, so that family should not be prioritized for LUTurbo-oriented follow-up.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0060.json:105:    "description": "Run one matched architecture probe on `jumprelu`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and the same runtime knobs, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `jumprelu`. Judge this probe by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `jumprelu` stays smooth and remains reasonably close to the `0.142923` `gated` anchor, it is worth keeping in reserve because its thresholded support path may reduce LUTurbo online selection overhead versus a full gating branch; if it is clearly worse across the curve, archive it as a non-promising matched alternative and return to the `gated` mainline next round.",
