research/history/round_summaries/round_0007.json:106:    "description": "\u7ee7\u7eed\u56f4\u7ed5 topk \u4e3b\u7ebf\u63a8\u8fdb\uff0c\u4e0d\u5f00\u65b0 family\uff0c\u4e0d\u6362\u4f18\u5316\u5668\uff0c\u4e0d\u52a8 K\u3002\u672c\u8f6e\u552f\u4e00\u4e3b\u53d8\u91cf\u4ecd\u662f\u5b66\u4e60\u7387\uff1a\u4ece 1.6e-3 \u4e0a\u8c03\u5230 1.8e-3\uff0c\u56de\u7b54\u201csignum+topk \u7684\u8f83\u4f18 LR \u662f\u5426\u4ecd\u5728 1.6e-3 \u4ee5\u4e0a\u201d\u8fd9\u4e2a\u5355\u4e00\u95ee\u9898\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0018.json:7:  "family_name": "topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0018.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Round 17 showed that `topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/EF=12` at `K=24` still descended smoothly through the late phase rather than flattening early, so the current recipe appears capacity-limited but still stable. This round changes only `K`, moving from `24` to `16`, to answer whether LUTurbo can reach the next allowed lower-cost point before reconstruction degradation becomes clearly impractical.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0018.json:20:    "summary": "Continue the active topk low-K frontier mapping: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and reduce `K` from `24` to `16` to test whether the deployable cost-quality frontier extends one more step down.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0018.json:23:    "family_name": "topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0018.json:25:    "self_review": "This stays on the active `topk` mainline, changes exactly one primary variable (`k`), respects the fixed `EF=12` and allowed-K constraints, and follows directly from the observed curve shape at `K=24`. The main risk is a steeper quality drop and higher dead-feature pressure at `K=16`, but `K=24` still showed smooth late improvement, so the next informative single question is whether the frontier boundary is at `K=16` or below `K=24`.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0018.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0018.json:30:        "value": "topk"
research/history/round_summaries/round_0018.json:53:      "For LUTurbo, this is still the most direct way to probe lower online selection and weighted-sum cost while staying within the same export-compatible topk recipe."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0018.json:57:      "If `K=16` degrades sharply or late-phase improvement largely disappears, treat `K=24` or `K=32` as the practical low-K boundary for this topk/signum regime.",
