research/history/round_summaries/round_0026.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Round 25 crashed with `first_step_timeout` while rerunning the exact K128 anchor, so the immediate question is not recipe quality but whether the timeout was caused by compile-time startup overhead rather than by the `topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/K=128/EF=12` recipe itself. This round changes only `COMPILE_MODEL`, turning it off on the exact reference backbone to test whether the baseline can complete cleanly and recover an interpretable curve.",
