research/history/round_summaries/round_0192.json:74:    "description": "\u6267\u884c\u4e00\u4e2a\u5408\u6cd5\u7684 matched architecture probe\uff1a\u5c06\u4e3b\u7ebf\u4ece lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual \u5207\u5230 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual\uff0c\u5176\u4f59 recipe \u4fdd\u6301 K=128\u3001EXPANSION_FACTOR=2\u3001OPTIMIZER=signum\u3001LR=3.0e-3 \u4e0d\u53d8\u3002\u8be5\u67b6\u6784\u7684\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u53ef\u5bfc\u51fa\u4e3a trunk \u9759\u6001\u5e93\u3001soft codebook \u9759\u6001\u5e93\u548c residual \u9759\u6001\u5b57\u5178\u4e0a\u7684\u6709\u9650\u52a0\u6743\u548c\uff0c\u5c5e\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\uff1b\u672c\u8f6e\u53ea\u56de\u7b54\u4e00\u4e2a\u95ee\u9898\uff0c\u5373\u53bb\u6389\u7b2c\u4e8c\u9636\u6bb5 residual refinement \u540e\uff0c\u8fd9\u4e2a family \u662f\u5426\u4ecd\u503c\u5f97\u7ee7\u7eed\u4fdd\u7559\u4e3a\u4f4e\u6210\u672c LUTurbo \u5019\u9009\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0055.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Round 54 completed the Hadamard-anchor LR localization: both adjacent callbacks around the current `gated@128` recipe (`LR=2.4e-3` in Round 53 and `LR=1.6e-3` in Round 54) stayed healthy but finished slightly worse than the `LR=2.0e-3` anchor, so the signum LR branch is now closed again. The next single question in the prescribed mainline order is therefore optimizer under the strengthened recipe: with `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, does swapping `signum` to `adam` now produce a healthier curve or competitive FVU, or does `gated` still clearly prefer `signum` even after preprocess improved conditioning?",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0055.json:20:    "summary": "Stay on the active `gated` mainline and return to the current family reference point. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`. Judge this run by the full trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `adam` now avoids the old mid-training blow-up and finishes competitively against the `0.142923` signum anchor, it earns exactly one LR callback on the same Hadamard recipe next; if it is flatter, noisier, or clearly worse again, lock `signum` as the optimizer for the strengthened `gated` mainline and stop the optimizer branch.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0055.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0055.json:104:    "description": "Stay on the active `gated` mainline and return to the current family reference point. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`. Judge this run by the full trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `adam` now avoids the old mid-training blow-up and finishes competitively against the `0.142923` signum anchor, it earns exactly one LR callback on the same Hadamard recipe next; if it is flatter, noisier, or clearly worse again, lock `signum` as the optimizer for the strengthened `gated` mainline and stop the optimizer branch.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0165.json:7:  "family_name": "lowrank_soft_codebook_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0165.json:17:    "hypothesis": "Matched architecture probe on lowrank_soft_codebook_residual with K=128, EXPANSION_FACTOR=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3 unchanged. Final reconstruction formula is x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_m pi_m c_m + \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i, where U(Vx) is a static low-rank trunk library, {c_m} is a static soft-codebook library, and {b_i} is a static residual dictionary. This is \u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9: LUTurbo can export it as trunk lookup + codebook lookup + one residual sparse lookup, all over fixed vector libraries. The single question for this probe is whether removing the second residual refinement stage keeps enough reconstruction quality to justify the lower encoder selection cost and likely lower runtime in the low-EF regime.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0165.json:18:    "summary": "Run a single matched architecture probe with ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_soft_codebook_residual while keeping K=128, EXPANSION_FACTOR=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, and LR=3.0e-3 fixed. The probe tests whether the simpler one-stage soft-codebook parent is still worth continuing as a lower-cost LUTurbo-compatible branch relative to the current two-stage mainline.",
