research/history/round_summaries/round_0165.json:34:      "This is a matched architecture probe that changes only ARCHITECTURE and stays safely within the known EF=2 selection-cost budget table.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0165.json:38:      "If FVU regresses materially versus the mainline while runtime savings are small, return to lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual next round and stop probing nearby parents.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0165.json:39:      "If runtime improves meaningfully at only modest FVU loss, keep lowrank_soft_codebook_residual as a cost-efficient compatible branch on the Pareto frontier, but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0019.json:7:  "family_name": "topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0019.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Round 18 showed that `topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/EF=12` at `K=16` still maintained a negative late-phase FVU slope instead of fully stalling, even though dead-feature pressure rose sharply. This round changes only `K`, moving from `16` to `8`, to answer whether the current export-compatible topk recipe can still support one more major cost reduction before reconstruction quality and compensation burden become clearly impractical.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0019.json:20:    "summary": "Continue the active topk low-K boundary search: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and reduce `K` from `16` to `8` to test whether the practical LUTurbo cost-quality frontier extends below `K=16`.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0019.json:23:    "family_name": "topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0019.json:25:    "self_review": "This stays on the active `topk` family, changes exactly one primary variable (`k`), respects the fixed `EF=12` rule and allowed-K set, and follows directly from the observed `K=16` curve shape. The main risk is that `K=8` may push the recipe past the useful regime, but `K=16` still improved through the end rather than hard-plateauing, so the next clean question is whether the true boundary sits at `K=8` or between `8` and `16`.",
