research/history/round_summaries/round_0166.json:17:    "hypothesis": "Matched architecture probe on lowrank_residual with K=128, EXPANSION_FACTOR=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3 unchanged. Final reconstruction formula is x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i, where U(Vx) is a static low-rank trunk library and {b_i} is a static residual dictionary. This is \u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9: LUTurbo can export it as one static trunk lookup plus one static sparse residual lookup over fixed vector libraries. The probe asks whether removing the soft-codebook coarse branch and second-stage refinement is still worth keeping as a materially cheaper, faster compatible architecture in the low-EF regime.",
