research/history/logs/agent_round_0212.stdout.log:1103:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family: topk\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d b_i \u6765\u81ea\u5355\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff1b\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u65f6\u4ecd\u662f\u5355\u6837\u672c top-k \u9009\u62e9\u540e\u7684\u5355\u5e93\u67e5\u8868\u4e0e\u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u5c5e\u4e8e\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u3002r208 \u5df2\u8bc1\u660e topk \u5728 EF=1\u3001K=64\u3001total_cost=0.31x \u4e0b\u80fd\u663e\u8457\u4f18\u4e8e\u6b64\u524d factorized_topk \u4f4e\u5f00\u9500\u70b9\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u672c\u8f6e\u4fdd\u6301 architecture=topk\u3001EXPANSION_FACTOR=1\u3001optimizer\u3001LR \u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u53ea\u628a K \u4ece 64 \u63d0\u5230 96\uff0c\u6cbf deployment \u6210\u672c\u8f74\u5728 <0.5x \u533a\u57df\u5185\u6362\u53d6\u66f4\u4f4e FVU\u3002\u9884\u8ba1 deployment cost \u7531\u7ea6 0.06x \u5347\u5230\u7ea6 0.09x\uff0ctotal_cost \u7ea6\u4e3a 0.34x\uff0c\u4ecd\u7a33\u5c45\u4f4e\u5f00\u9500\u533a\uff0c\u540c\u65f6\u6709\u671b\u660e\u663e\u6539\u5584\u5f53\u524d 0.2583 \u7684 FVU\u3002",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0212.stdout.log:1104:    "summary": "\u56fa\u5b9a topk \u7684 EF=1\u3001signum\u3001LR=3e-3\uff0c\u53ea\u5c06 K \u4ece 64 \u63d0\u5347\u5230 96\uff0c\u76ee\u6807\u662f\u5728\u7ea6 0.34x \u603b\u6210\u672c\u5904\u83b7\u5f97\u4e00\u4e2a\u6bd4\u5f53\u524d 0.31x \u70b9\u66f4\u4f4e FVU \u7684\u65b0\u4f4e\u5f00\u9500 Pareto \u5019\u9009\u3002",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0212.stdout.log:1109:class LowRankFactorizedResidualSparseCoder(SparseCoder):
research/history/logs/agent_round_0212.stdout.log:1152:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family: lowrank_factorized_residual\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_r beta_r u_r + \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d u_r \u662f\u9759\u6001 trunk \u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff0cb_i \u662f\u9759\u6001 residual \u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff1b\u5728\u7ebf\u4fa7\u53ea\u8ba1\u7b97\u7cfb\u6570 beta_r \u4e0e alpha_i\uff0c\u5e76\u5728 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7aef\u5bfc\u51fa\u4e3a\u4e24\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\u4e0a\u7684\u6709\u9650\u52a0\u6743\u548c\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u5c5e\u4e8e\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u3002r209 \u5bf9 topk@EF1,K96 \u7684\u7ee7\u7eed\u52a0\u5927\u67e5\u8868\u9884\u7b97\u88ab policy \u62e6\u622a\uff0c\u8bf4\u660e\u5355\u7eaf\u6cbf topk \u7684 K \u8f74\u4e0a\u63a2\u4e0d\u7a33\uff1b\u672c\u8f6e\u4fdd\u6301 K=64\u3001EF=1\u3001optimizer\u3001LR \u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u53ea\u628a architecture \u4ece topk \u5207\u5230 lowrank_factorized_residual\uff0c\u6d4b\u8bd5\u5728\u4ecd\u7784\u51c6 <0.5x \u533a\u57df\u7684\u524d\u63d0\u4e0b\uff0c\u52a0\u5165\u6781\u8f7b low-rank trunk \u4e0e factorized residual scorer \u540e\uff0c\u662f\u5426\u80fd\u663e\u8457\u4f18\u4e8e topk@0.31x \u7684 FVU\u3002\u6309\u73b0\u6709\u6210\u672c\u8868\u5916\u63a8\uff0c\u8be5\u914d\u7f6e\u6709\u5e0c\u671b\u843d\u5728\u4f4e\u5f00\u9500\u533a\u6216\u5176\u8fb9\u754c\u9644\u8fd1\uff0c\u540c\u65f6\u63d0\u4f9b\u6bd4\u7eaf\u5355\u5e93 topk \u66f4\u5f3a\u7684\u8868\u8fbe\u3002",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0212.stdout.log:1153:    "summary": "\u5207\u6362\u5230\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u7684 lowrank_factorized_residual\uff0c\u56fa\u5b9a K=64\u3001EF=1\u3001signum\u3001LR=3e-3\uff0c\u53ea\u6539\u53d8 architecture\uff0c\u9a8c\u8bc1\u8f7b\u91cf trunk+residual \u7ed3\u6784\u80fd\u5426\u5728\u4f4e\u5f00\u9500\u533a\u9644\u8fd1\u62ff\u5230\u660e\u663e\u4f18\u4e8e topk \u7684 FVU\u3002",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0212.stdout.log:1155:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_factorized_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"TRUNK_RANK","value":"32"}],"expected_win":"lower_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: lowrank_factorized_residual。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_r beta_r u_r + Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 {u_r} 是静态 trunk 向量库、{b_i} 是静态 residual 向量库；factorized scorer 只影响在线选择与系数计算，不改变 decoder 端的静态库有限加权和形式，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”链路，兼容性为扩展兼容。单主变量选择 TRUNK_RANK：在保持 ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_factorized_residual、K=64、EF=1、signum、LR=3e-3 不变时，把 trunk_rank 从当前 auto≈128 下调到 32，测试当前 0.69x 点的主要冗余是否来自过大的 trunk 库；若 trunk 只是提供粗补偿而 residual 分支已承担主要表达，则可把 encoder+deployment 总成本一口气压入 <0.5x 区域，同时维持明显优于 topk@0.31x 的 FVU。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 TRUNK_RANK=32 仍保持明显优于 topk@EF1,K64 的 FVU 且进入 <0.5x，则固定该 family 后只沿 K 轴做一次补点。","如果 TRUNK_RANK=32 的 FVU 退化过大，则说明该 family 的收益高度依赖 trunk 容量，低开销主战场应回到更短链路的 topk 或新的轻量单库方案。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_factorized_residual 的导出形式稳定为 trunk 静态库 + residual 静态库的有限加权和，属于扩展兼容，可继续保留在兼容 frontier 候选集中。","r210 在 0.69x 处取得 0.1256 FVU，且 tokens_per_sec≈166.6k、总耗时 291s，明显快于近期 topk/soft-codebook 线；因此优先压缩 trunk_rank 比继续增大 K 更符合当前低开销与训练成本双目标。"],"primary_variable":"other_param","self_review":"这轮只改一个主轴 TRUNK_RANK，归因干净，且直接针对 r210 暴露出的成本结构问题。选择 32 而不是 64，是因为 64 大概率仍停留在 >0.5x 边界外；32 才有机会真正补上当前最缺的 <0.5x 前沿，但风险是 trunk 过度压缩后 FVU 可能明显反弹。","summary":"在扩展兼容的 lowrank_factorized_residual 上做一次低开销 param-only 探索：固定 K=64、EF=1、signum、LR=3e-3，仅把 TRUNK_RANK 压到 32，目标是在保留 trunk+residual 双库导出形式的同时，把当前 0.69x 候选推进到 <0.5x 区域。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0052.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 51 completed the downward K mapping: the strengthened `gated` recipe (`signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`) now owns every allowed frontier point from `K=128` down to `K=4`. With the K axis fully mapped, the next single question is whether the most deployment-stressed point is slightly overdriven: if we keep the same `gated@4` recipe fixed and lower only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3`, does the ultra-low-K training curve become smoother and finish lower, or is `2.0e-3` still the right setting even at the minimum support?","summary":"Stay on the active `gated` family and hold the newly established minimum-support point fixed at `K=4` with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3` to test whether the current ultra-low-K recipe is mildly overstepping rather than capacity-limited. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if the lower LR reduces early noise and yields a better finish than the current `gated@4` result (`0.447286`), then low-K gated wants a different step size than the `K=128` anchor; if the curve slows uniformly or the endpoint worsens, keep `2.0e-3` as the shared mainline LR across the whole K grid.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `lr`. It also avoids reopening the K axis now that the allowed grid has been completely mapped and instead asks the highest-value remaining recipe question at the most stressed deployment point. The main risk is that the poorer ultra-low-K quality is mostly capacity-driven rather than step-size-driven, but a single LR callback at `K=4` is the cleanest way to distinguish those explanations without introducing another family or coupled change.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"4"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 51 completed the full allowed-K sweep for the improved `gated` recipe: it now holds frontier points at `K=4,8,16,24,32,64,96,128` under `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`.","Round 52 returns from K mapping to recipe refinement and isolates the LR question specifically at `K=4`, where LUTurbo online cost is minimal and training dynamics are most likely to expose over-aggressive step size."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated@4` improves with `LR=1.6e-3`, run at most one nearby LR confirmation on the same `K=4` recipe to localize the low-K optimum.","If `LR=1.6e-3` is worse or only slower, keep `2.0e-3` as the shared mainline LR and consider the remaining low-K gap primarily a capacity issue rather than a tuning issue."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
