research/history/logs/agent_round_0036.stdout.log:55:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The `gated` family may only be competitive at the largest support, so stepping `K` down from `128` to `96` while holding `EF=12`, `optimizer=signum`, and `lr=1.6e-3` tests one question only: does `gated` remain competitive on the adjacent frontier point, or is its apparent edge confined to `K=128`?","summary":"Round 35 answered the preprocess probe: Hadamard did not improve the anchored `gated` recipe, leaving no meaningful recipe knobs unexplored in the prescribed order. The next single-variable move is therefore `K`. Use the plain `gated` anchor and drop only `K` to `96`. This is the highest-value neighboring check because there is already a strong `topk` control at `K=96` (`0.171856`), so the run directly tells us whether `gated` has broader family viability or whether it should be treated as a narrow `K=128` specialization. Read the curve shape as well as the endpoint: if `gated@96` is smooth and beats or matches the `topk@96` control comfortably, keep the family alive across K; if it is clearly worse or unstable, treat `gated` as exhausted outside the single `K=128` point.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This keeps the same family, preserves EF at 12, changes exactly one primary variable (`K`), and only moves K after the LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess probes failed to improve the anchored recipe. Choosing `K=96` minimizes extrapolation because it is adjacent to the current gated anchor and has a matched topk frontier point for direct comparison.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 36 begins the first K probe for gated after recipe tuning was exhausted: gated, K=96, EF=12, signum, LR=1.6e-3.","Compare gated@96 against the existing topk@96 control and judge curve shape, not just terminal FVU; this determines whether gated generalizes beyond the isolated K=128 win."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated@96` is competitive with or better than `topk@96`, gated deserves at least one more K-mapping round within the allowed grid.","If `gated@96` clearly trails `topk@96`, stop spending mainline rounds on gated except as the recorded K=128 incumbent."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0064.stdout.log:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With the `gated` mainline stalled for eleven rounds and the lighter selector probes `group_topk` and `bucketed_topk` both coming back clearly worse, the next highest-value matched architecture probe is `codebook_topk`: it remains LUTurbo-compatible because the reconstruction is still a finite sum over static libraries, but it changes the architecture by adding a hard coarse codebook selection before the sparse residual. This round answers one question only: under the matched `K=128`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EF=12` recipe, is `codebook_topk` intrinsically strong enough to justify any later follow-up, or should it be ruled out immediately.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `codebook_topk` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"codebook_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 64 policy by changing exactly one primary variable: architecture. `codebook_topk` is a better remaining probe than batch-coupled variants because it stays single-sample deployable, and it is more informative than heavier multi-branch gating because it tests a distinct static-library decomposition pattern that could plausibly trade some sparse support work for a coarse lookup plus residual correction.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"codebook_topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 64 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `codebook_topk` after `group_topk` and `bucketed_topk` both failed to beat the matched `gated` control.","`codebook_topk` is extended-compatible with LUTurbo because the final reconstruction can be exported as a hard-selected static coarse codebook vector plus a finite weighted sum over a static residual decoder library.","Judge this probe strictly as a family-worthiness test against matched `gated` K128: if it is clearly worse, discard it and return to the `gated` mainline next round; if it is competitive, record the result but still return to the mainline per policy."],"next_hypotheses":["If `codebook_topk` is clearly worse than matched `gated`, discard the family and return to the `gated` mainline next round.","If `codebook_topk` is roughly competitive, record it as a possible coarse-plus-residual deployment direction but still return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy.","If `codebook_topk` unexpectedly beats matched `gated`, schedule at most one later follow-up after the mandated return to the `gated` mainline."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
