research/history/logs/agent_action_0196.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"候选 probe family 的最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i；其中 {b_i} 是单个静态字典库中的固定向量，alpha_i 是由低秩 factorized scorer 在线选择得到的稀疏系数。factorized scorer 只改变选择路径，不改变 decoder 端的单库有限加权和形式，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的‘查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿’推理链路，兼容性为直接兼容。主假设：在保持 K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 完全 matched 的前提下，factorized_topk 是否能以更低 encoder selection cost（约 0.38x h×n）保留足够可用的 FVU；若其相对 topk 仍无实用优势，则说明单库 factorized selector 在当前低 EF regime 下也不值得继续占用主线注意力。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 factorized_topk 仍明显劣于 lowrank_residual / lowrank_soft_codebook_residual，则下一轮回到主线，只调一个成本轴如 TRUNK_RANK、NUM_CODES 或 STAGE1_RATIO。","若 factorized_topk 相比 topk 以更低选择成本获得更好或接近的 FVU 且训练更快，可将其保留为最便宜的直接兼容 selector 支线。","继续避免 routed 与 bucketed matched probe，因为它们在 EF=2 下 selection_cost 超过 1.5×h×n 预算。"],"notes_to_memory":["本轮是 matched architecture probe；除 architecture 外保持 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变。","factorized_topk 的导出路径是单一静态字典库上的有限稀疏加权和，属直接兼容。","r195 已确认 plain topk 在当前 regime 下 FVU=0.1755 且被 discard；本轮进一步验证更低成本的 factorized selector 是否值得保留。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"这是一个严格单变量的 matched probe，科学问题清晰：最便宜的直接兼容 factorized 单库架构是否还有 LUTurbo 价值。它不改变部署公式，只隔离 selector 低秩化本身的效果，适合在连续多轮 probe 后给单库路线一个更完整的结论。","summary":"执行一个 matched architecture probe：将主线切到 factorized_topk，其余 recipe 保持 K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变。该架构的最终重构是单一静态字典库上的有限稀疏加权和，属直接兼容；本轮只回答一个问题，即低秩 factorized selector 是否足以让最便宜的单库 LUTurbo 方案继续值得保留。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0078.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`two_stage_residual` has stalled at the matched `K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=2.0e-3` anchor after several clean recipe checks and three weaker simple-family probes. A single matched probe on `lowrank_two_stage_residual` is the highest-value architecture question now: it preserves the same staged static-library decomposition contract while adding a stronger coarse low-rank trunk. If it cannot beat or clearly pressure the current `two_stage_residual` anchor under the exact same recipe, then the added coarse-path complexity is not worth continuing in this regime.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching only `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_two_stage_residual` while keeping the current `two_stage_residual` reference recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and baseline aux settings. This answers one question only: whether a stronger low-rank coarse stage is worth revisiting at all, or whether the simpler `two_stage_residual` should remain the active LUTurbo-aligned mainline.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is policy-clean: one matched architecture probe, one primary variable, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` is explicitly pinned. The main tradeoff is that `lowrank_two_stage_residual` likely raises online coefficient cost versus the current mainline, so it is only worth continuing if the FVU gain is material rather than marginal. I am choosing it over another simple selector family because recent matched probes already showed that lighter alternatives are clearly behind the current anchor.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 78 uses the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_two_stage_residual` against the exact `two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Interpretation rule: because `lowrank_two_stage_residual` adds online coarse-path compute, only a clear reconstruction win justifies future follow-up; a near-tie should still count against reopening this family."],"next_hypotheses":["Return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless, per the operator instruction.","If `lowrank_two_stage_residual` wins clearly, schedule exactly one clean confirmation round on that family before any LR or optimizer tuning.","If it loses or is only marginally better, treat the current stall as evidence that stronger coarse-trunk complexity is not the right next direction under the K128/EF12 LUTurbo-aligned regime."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
