research/history/logs/agent_round_0058.stdout.log:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With the `gated` mainline now stable but non-improving for five rounds, the highest-value single matched architecture probe is the simplest directly compatible alternative: `topk`. It preserves LUTurbo's static-vector finite weighted-sum export form while potentially lowering online selection and coefficient cost relative to `gated`, so this round asks one clean yes/no question: under the exact current mainline recipe (`K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`), is `topk` competitive enough in full-curve behavior to be worth revisiting as a family, or does `gated` remain clearly superior even before runtime considerations are counted?","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `topk`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and the same runtime knobs, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `topk`. Judge this probe by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `topk` stays smooth and closes most of the gap to the `0.142923` `gated` anchor, it is still worth later family-level consideration because its deployment path is simpler; if it is clearly worse across the curve, archive it as a non-promising matched alternative and return to the `gated` mainline next round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 58 matched-probe rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping `K`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, and the rest of the settled mainline recipe fixed. `topk` is the best probe candidate because it remains directly export-compatible for LUTurbo and offers a simpler online path than `gated`; the main risk is that reusing the `gated`-tuned recipe may understate topk's ceiling, but that is acceptable here because this round is explicitly a family-worthiness screen, not a new topk tuning campaign.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 58 is a single matched architecture probe inserted after five consecutive non-improving `gated` rounds; it must be judged only as a family-worthiness test, and the next round should return to the `gated` mainline regardless of outcome.","`topk` is directly compatible with LUTurbo deployment because the reconstruction remains a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library with fixed `K`; compared with `gated`, it may also lower online selection and coefficient-computation cost if quality remains competitive.","Judge this probe by full curve shape and endpoint relative to the current `gated@128` anchor: if `topk` is clearly worse across the trajectory, archive it under the current matched recipe; if it is competitive, record that as evidence that the simpler architecture may still deserve a later dedicated revisit."],"next_hypotheses":["If matched `topk` is clearly worse than the strengthened `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round and treat this probe as closed.","If matched `topk` is roughly competitive with a healthy curve, still return to the `gated` mainline next round, but keep one later topk revisit available because its simpler deployment path may outweigh a small training-quality gap.","If matched `topk` unexpectedly beats the current `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy but schedule exactly one later topk follow-up under its own lane."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
