research/history/logs/agent_round_0058.stdout.log:147:research/history/round_summaries/round_0036.json:20:    "summary": "Round 35 answered the preprocess probe: Hadamard did not improve the anchored `gated` recipe, leaving no meaningful recipe knobs unexplored in the prescribed order. The next single-variable move is therefore `K`. Use the plain `gated` anchor and drop only `K` to `96`. This is the highest-value neighboring check because there is already a strong `topk` control at `K=96` (`0.171856`), so the run directly tells us whether `gated` has broader family viability or whether it should be treated as a narrow `K=128` specialization. Read the curve shape as well as the endpoint: if `gated@96` is smooth and beats or matches the `topk@96` control comfortably, keep the family alive across K; if it is clearly worse or unstable, treat `gated` as exhausted outside the single `K=128` point.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0058.stdout.log:148:research/history/round_summaries/round_0036.json:25:    "self_review": "This keeps the same family, preserves EF at 12, changes exactly one primary variable (`K`), and only moves K after the LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess probes failed to improve the anchored recipe. Choosing `K=96` minimizes extrapolation because it is adjacent to the current gated anchor and has a matched topk frontier point for direct comparison.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0058.stdout.log:150:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With the `gated` mainline now stable but non-improving for five rounds, the highest-value single matched architecture probe is the simplest directly compatible alternative: `topk`. It preserves LUTurbo's static-vector finite weighted-sum export form while potentially lowering online selection and coefficient cost relative to `gated`, so this round asks one clean yes/no question: under the exact current mainline recipe (`K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`), is `topk` competitive enough in full-curve behavior to be worth revisiting as a family, or does `gated` remain clearly superior even before runtime considerations are counted?","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `topk`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and the same runtime knobs, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `topk`. Judge this probe by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `topk` stays smooth and closes most of the gap to the `0.142923` `gated` anchor, it is still worth later family-level consideration because its deployment path is simpler; if it is clearly worse across the curve, archive it as a non-promising matched alternative and return to the `gated` mainline next round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 58 matched-probe rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping `K`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, and the rest of the settled mainline recipe fixed. `topk` is the best probe candidate because it remains directly export-compatible for LUTurbo and offers a simpler online path than `gated`; the main risk is that reusing the `gated`-tuned recipe may understate topk's ceiling, but that is acceptable here because this round is explicitly a family-worthiness screen, not a new topk tuning campaign.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 58 is a single matched architecture probe inserted after five consecutive non-improving `gated` rounds; it must be judged only as a family-worthiness test, and the next round should return to the `gated` mainline regardless of outcome.","`topk` is directly compatible with LUTurbo deployment because the reconstruction remains a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library with fixed `K`; compared with `gated`, it may also lower online selection and coefficient-computation cost if quality remains competitive.","Judge this probe by full curve shape and endpoint relative to the current `gated@128` anchor: if `topk` is clearly worse across the trajectory, archive it under the current matched recipe; if it is competitive, record that as evidence that the simpler architecture may still deserve a later dedicated revisit."],"next_hypotheses":["If matched `topk` is clearly worse than the strengthened `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round and treat this probe as closed.","If matched `topk` is roughly competitive with a healthy curve, still return to the `gated` mainline next round, but keep one later topk revisit available because its simpler deployment path may outweigh a small training-quality gap.","If matched `topk` unexpectedly beats the current `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy but schedule exactly one later topk follow-up under its own lane."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0039.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 38 cleanly reproduced the `gated` anchor at `K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=1.6e-3` with the same still-improving late curve, while the only prior LR callback (`1.2e-3`) was uniformly worse. The next single question is therefore whether the current recipe is slightly underdriven rather than overdriven: does a modest LR increase to `2.0e-3` improve the full training trajectory and beat the refreshed anchor?","summary":"Continue on the same `gated` mainline and probe only the learning-rate axis. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed, explicitly pin the reference aux/runtime knobs, and raise `LR` from `1.6e-3` to `2.0e-3`. Read the whole curve, not just terminal FVU: if the higher LR preserves stability while improving mid-to-late descent below the refreshed `0.149936` control, then the current anchor was slightly conservative; if it becomes noisier or finishes worse, keep `1.6e-3` as the gated LR anchor and stop the LR branch.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and changes exactly one core variable: `lr`. It also follows the prescribed order now that the clean baseline has been backfilled successfully. The main risk is that `2.0e-3` could overdrive training, but the evidence so far points the other way: `1.2e-3` was clearly slower/worse, and the refreshed `1.6e-3` baseline was still improving late.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 38 confirmed the clean `gated@128` control reproduces the anchor almost exactly and still shows late improvement, so baseline reproducibility is no longer the blocker.","Round 39 reopens the LR axis cleanly on the same `gated` mainline by testing an upward callback to `LR=2.0e-3` after the earlier downward callback to `1.2e-3` was uniformly worse."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated` at `LR=2.0e-3` improves the trajectory or final FVU while remaining stable, run one final nearby LR confirmation before moving on to optimizer or K.","If `gated` at `LR=2.0e-3` is noisier or worse than the refreshed control, lock `LR=1.6e-3` as the gated mainline anchor and move to the next prescribed recipe axis."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0108.stdout.log:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 107 was the first signum LR probe on `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` to beat the archived `LR=2.0e-3` K128 baseline, so before opening the optimizer branch the next single question should be whether `LR=2.4e-3` is a reproducible new anchor rather than a one-off improvement. Re-running the exact `LR=2.4e-3` recipe is the cleanest way to judge whether the full curve remains stronger than the `LR=2.0e-3` and `LR=1.6e-3` runs, especially in early/mid descent and late stability, rather than trusting the endpoint alone.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and rerun the promising higher-LR recipe with `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.4e-3`, changing no other recipe variable.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"confirm_baseline","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays within the same family, keeps `K` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and isolates the only unresolved mainline recipe axis: whether `LR=2.4e-3` is the right signum operating point. The tradeoff is spending one more round before opening the optimizer branch, but that is justified because optimizer comparisons should use a settled signum anchor rather than an unconfirmed one-off LR win.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 108 retries the improved `LR=2.4e-3` signum probe for `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=128` and `EF=12` to determine whether the gain over `LR=2.0e-3` is reproducible.","Judge this run by curve-shape repeatability versus the archived `LR=2.0e-3`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and Round 107 `LR=2.4e-3` runs, not by endpoint alone.","Only after resolving whether `LR=2.4e-3` is a stable signum anchor should the optimizer branch open on this family."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=2.4e-3` reproduces the stronger curve or endpoint, promote it to the operative signum mainline LR and test `OPTIMIZER=adam` next at that settled recipe.","If the `LR=2.4e-3` repeat falls back to a near-tie or worse than `LR=2.0e-3`, close the signum LR branch with `LR=2.0e-3` as the operative anchor and test `OPTIMIZER=adam` next there.","Do not change loss, preprocess, or `K` until the optimizer question has been isolated from the settled signum baseline."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
