research/history/logs/agent_round_0039.stdout.log:77:    "summary": "Run a clean control on the current `gated` mainline reference recipe. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=1.6e-3`, and explicitly lock the known reference aux/runtime settings so the next comparison is grounded in a fresh, fully specified anchor curve. Judge this run by the whole trajectory, not just terminal FVU: recent `gated` runs at `K=96` and `K=64` were still improving late, so we need a refreshed `K=128` control before deciding whether to continue down the K ladder or revisit LR.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0039.stdout.log:102:research/history/logs/agent_action_0036.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The `gated` family may only be competitive at the largest support, so stepping `K` down from `128` to `96` while holding `EF=12`, `optimizer=signum`, and `lr=1.6e-3` tests one question only: does `gated` remain competitive on the adjacent frontier point, or is its apparent edge confined to `K=128`?","summary":"Round 35 answered the preprocess probe: Hadamard did not improve the anchored `gated` recipe, leaving no meaningful recipe knobs unexplored in the prescribed order. The next single-variable move is therefore `K`. Use the plain `gated` anchor and drop only `K` to `96`. This is the highest-value neighboring check because there is already a strong `topk` control at `K=96` (`0.171856`), so the run directly tells us whether `gated` has broader family viability or whether it should be treated as a narrow `K=128` specialization. Read the curve shape as well as the endpoint: if `gated@96` is smooth and beats or matches the `topk@96` control comfortably, keep the family alive across K; if it is clearly worse or unstable, treat `gated` as exhausted outside the single `K=128` point.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This keeps the same family, preserves EF at 12, changes exactly one primary variable (`K`), and only moves K after the LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess probes failed to improve the anchored recipe. Choosing `K=96` minimizes extrapolation because it is adjacent to the current gated anchor and has a matched topk frontier point for direct comparison.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 36 begins the first K probe for gated after recipe tuning was exhausted: gated, K=96, EF=12, signum, LR=1.6e-3.","Compare gated@96 against the existing topk@96 control and judge curve shape, not just terminal FVU; this determines whether gated generalizes beyond the isolated K=128 win."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated@96` is competitive with or better than `topk@96`, gated deserves at least one more K-mapping round within the allowed grid.","If `gated@96` clearly trails `topk@96`, stop spending mainline rounds on gated except as the recorded K=128 incumbent."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0039.stdout.log:104:research/history/round_summaries/round_0037.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Because `gated` beat the matched `topk` control at `K=96`, the next single question is whether that advantage extends one more step down the support ladder; testing `ARCHITECTURE=gated, K=64, EF=12, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=1.6e-3` will show whether `gated` is broadly stronger across high-K frontier points or only wins near the very top end.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0039.stdout.log:107:research/history/logs/agent_action_0032.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With `gated` held at `K=128, EF=12` and the signum anchor LR restored to `1.6e-3`, swapping the optimizer from `signum` to `adam` tests whether the current gated route is optimizer-limited rather than LR-limited; this round asks only whether `adam` produces a better-shaped training curve and a competitive or improved terminal FVU versus the `signum` baseline.","summary":"Round 31 answered the first LR callback cleanly enough: lowering LR to `1.2e-3` made `gated` worse (`0.15385`), so `1.6e-3` remains the best anchored recipe inside the family. Following the required order, the next single-variable move is the optimizer swap. Keep architecture, K, EF, and LR fixed, then judge `adam` by trajectory shape as much as the endpoint: if it descends faster early and remains smoother without late instability, `gated` may want a different optimizer; if it is noisier, flatter, or simply worse throughout, `signum` stays the preferred optimizer for this family.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This changes exactly one main variable, `optimizer`, while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EF=12`, and the anchored LR at `1.6e-3`. It follows the prescribed sequence after the initial downward LR callback failed, and it keeps the investigation on the same family rather than opening a new branch.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 31 showed gated+signum prefers LR=1.6e-3 over 1.2e-3, so the signum anchor remains the current gated reference recipe.","Round 32 should test the optimizer swap directly: gated, K=128, EF=12, LR=1.6e-3, optimizer=adam; evaluate curve smoothness and late-stage stability, not just final FVU."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated+adam` is competitive or better with a healthier curve, run exactly one LR callback for adam next to localize its usable range.","If `gated+adam` is clearly worse than `gated+signum`, keep signum as the gated optimizer and only then consider loss/preprocess adjustments before touching K."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0039.stdout.log:109:research/history/round_summaries/round_0036.json:20:    "summary": "Round 35 answered the preprocess probe: Hadamard did not improve the anchored `gated` recipe, leaving no meaningful recipe knobs unexplored in the prescribed order. The next single-variable move is therefore `K`. Use the plain `gated` anchor and drop only `K` to `96`. This is the highest-value neighboring check because there is already a strong `topk` control at `K=96` (`0.171856`), so the run directly tells us whether `gated` has broader family viability or whether it should be treated as a narrow `K=128` specialization. Read the curve shape as well as the endpoint: if `gated@96` is smooth and beats or matches the `topk@96` control comfortably, keep the family alive across K; if it is clearly worse or unstable, treat `gated` as exhausted outside the single `K=128` point.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0039.stdout.log:112:research/history/round_summaries/round_0036.json:76:    "description": "Round 35 answered the preprocess probe: Hadamard did not improve the anchored `gated` recipe, leaving no meaningful recipe knobs unexplored in the prescribed order. The next single-variable move is therefore `K`. Use the plain `gated` anchor and drop only `K` to `96`. This is the highest-value neighboring check because there is already a strong `topk` control at `K=96` (`0.171856`), so the run directly tells us whether `gated` has broader family viability or whether it should be treated as a narrow `K=128` specialization. Read the curve shape as well as the endpoint: if `gated@96` is smooth and beats or matches the `topk@96` control comfortably, keep the family alive across K; if it is clearly worse or unstable, treat `gated` as exhausted outside the single `K=128` point.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0039.stdout.log:169:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 38 cleanly reproduced the `gated` anchor at `K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=1.6e-3` with the same still-improving late curve, while the only prior LR callback (`1.2e-3`) was uniformly worse. The next single question is therefore whether the current recipe is slightly underdriven rather than overdriven: does a modest LR increase to `2.0e-3` improve the full training trajectory and beat the refreshed anchor?","summary":"Continue on the same `gated` mainline and probe only the learning-rate axis. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed, explicitly pin the reference aux/runtime knobs, and raise `LR` from `1.6e-3` to `2.0e-3`. Read the whole curve, not just terminal FVU: if the higher LR preserves stability while improving mid-to-late descent below the refreshed `0.149936` control, then the current anchor was slightly conservative; if it becomes noisier or finishes worse, keep `1.6e-3` as the gated LR anchor and stop the LR branch.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and changes exactly one core variable: `lr`. It also follows the prescribed order now that the clean baseline has been backfilled successfully. The main risk is that `2.0e-3` could overdrive training, but the evidence so far points the other way: `1.2e-3` was clearly slower/worse, and the refreshed `1.6e-3` baseline was still improving late.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 38 confirmed the clean `gated@128` control reproduces the anchor almost exactly and still shows late improvement, so baseline reproducibility is no longer the blocker.","Round 39 reopens the LR axis cleanly on the same `gated` mainline by testing an upward callback to `LR=2.0e-3` after the earlier downward callback to `1.2e-3` was uniformly worse."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated` at `LR=2.0e-3` improves the trajectory or final FVU while remaining stable, run one final nearby LR confirmation before moving on to optimizer or K.","If `gated` at `LR=2.0e-3` is noisier or worse than the refreshed control, lock `LR=1.6e-3` as the gated mainline anchor and move to the next prescribed recipe axis."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0128.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"NUM_CODES","value":"32"}],"expected_win":"lower_selection_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。其中 U(Vx) 可导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{c_m} 为静态 soft-codebook 库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此最终仍是多个静态向量库上的有限加权和，可落到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的‘查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿’推理链路，兼容性为扩展兼容。r127 的 matched probe 说明两阶段 refinement 在 EF=2 下仍有真实 FVU 价值，但其 selection_cost 明显高于单阶段父节点；因此本轮回到主线 family，只改 NUM_CODES=32，测试是否能在保持两阶段结构优势的同时压低 encoder 选择成本，缩小与 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 的成本差距。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 NUM_CODES=32 仅小幅伤害 FVU 但显著降低 selection_cost，则继续沿 num_codes 轴补一个中间点细化 Pareto。","若 NUM_CODES=32 明显恶化 FVU 且时间收益有限，则恢复默认 code 配方，转向 STAGE1_RATIO 或 preprocess/loss 轴。","若 NUM_CODES=32 维持接近主线 FVU 且训练更快，则把它作为两阶段 family 的低成本变体保留在兼容 frontier 候选中。"],"notes_to_memory":["本轮已从 matched architecture probe 回到主线 family，遵守‘probe 后下一轮回主线’规则。","两阶段 family 的兼容性与导出路径不变：trunk 库 + soft-codebook 库 + residual 字典库。","本轮只改 NUM_CODES，目标不是追更低绝对 FVU，而是测试两阶段主线能否改善 selection_cost/FVU Pareto。","评估时必须同时记录 selection_cost、FVU、总耗时、tokens_per_sec、final_total_tokens，避免把更长训练误判为结构收益。"],"primary_variable":"num_codes","self_review":"本轮严格保持 architecture、K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变，只改一个会直接影响 encoder 成本的主变量，符合主线推进和单变量原则。风险在于 NUM_CODES=32 可能过于激进，但这一步最直接检验两阶段主线是否还有内部降本空间。","summary":"回到 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 主线，固定 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3，仅下调 NUM_CODES 到 32，测试两阶段结构能否在保留主要 FVU 优势的同时降低选择成本。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0041.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 40 answered the LR question cleanly: `LR=2.4e-3` preserved a smooth curve but regressed slightly versus the new `2.0e-3` anchor, so the signum LR branch is now sufficiently localized around `2.0e-3`. The next single question in the prescribed order is therefore optimizer: with `ARCHITECTURE=gated, K=128, EF=12, LR=2.0e-3` fixed at the refreshed anchor recipe, does swapping `signum` to `adam` produce a healthier curve or competitive FVU, or does `gated` still clearly prefer `signum`?","summary":"Keep the active `gated` family and move to the optimizer axis now that the LR sweep has identified `2.0e-3` as the best current signum setting. Run `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.0e-3` with all reference aux/runtime knobs explicitly pinned, and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`. Judge the result by the whole trajectory, not just endpoint: if `adam` descends more cleanly or closes the gap at the stronger `2.0e-3` anchor, it earns exactly one LR callback next; if it is flatter, noisier, or clearly worse again, lock `signum` as the gated optimizer and stop the optimizer branch.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same mainline family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and changes exactly one core variable: `optimizer`. It follows the stated round order after the LR branch produced a modest win at `2.0e-3` and a slight regression at `2.4e-3`, which is enough evidence to stop spending more rounds on signum LR micro-tuning before checking optimizer. The main risk is that `adam` was already poor at `1.6e-3`, but that makes this a bounded confirmation rather than an open-ended sweep.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 40 slightly regressed from the `LR=2.0e-3` gated anchor while keeping a similarly smooth, still-improving curve, so the signum LR branch is localized enough to move on.","Round 41 switches the current `gated@128` anchor from `signum` to `adam` at fixed `LR=2.0e-3` to answer the next prescribed optimizer question under the updated mainline recipe rather than the older `1.6e-3` anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated+adam` at `LR=2.0e-3` is competitive or better with a healthy curve, run exactly one Adam LR callback next to test whether its usable range differs from signum.","If `gated+adam` at `LR=2.0e-3` is clearly worse again, keep `signum` as the gated optimizer and move on to the next recipe axis without further optimizer work."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0151.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"该 matched probe 的最终重构公式为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_i alpha_i b_i。其中 U(Vx) 可导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此最终仍是静态向量库上的有限加权和，可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。与当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 相比，这个 probe 只移除 soft-codebook coarse branch 与第二阶段 residual refinement，保持 K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 与其余主 recipe 不变，因此只回答一个问题：在当前低 EF 预算内，soft-codebook + two-stage 这套更重结构是否真的提供了足够大的质量收益，值得相对 lowrank_residual 更高的 encoder 选择成本与部署查表成本。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 lowrank_residual 在显著更低 selection_cost 与 deploy 成本下仅小幅损失 FVU，则说明当前主线的复杂结构优势不足以覆盖其总成本，下一轮按规则回到主线后应谨慎继续投入该 family。","若 lowrank_residual 明显更差，则说明不仅第二阶段 refinement 有价值，soft-codebook coarse branch 本身也在 EF=2 下提供了必要结构收益，下一轮回到主线继续做主线 recipe/成本工作。","若 lowrank_residual 终点更差但训练明显更快，则把它记为更便宜的兼容对照点，但不在本轮直接替换主线。"],"notes_to_memory":["本轮是单次 matched architecture probe，严格只改 architecture，其余 K、EF、optimizer、LR 全部与主线参考配方一致。","lowrank_residual 属于扩展兼容 family，不属于不兼容候选，可合法进入兼容 frontier 对照。","r150 已表明仅去掉第二阶段后的 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 仍明显落后于主线；本轮进一步测试若连 soft-codebook coarse branch 一并去掉，性能是否会继续明显下滑。","评估时必须同时记录 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时、final_total_tokens，区分是结构更简单带来的吞吐提升，还是确有更好的总成本-质量权衡。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"遵守本轮架构探针规则：只改 architecture，保持主线的 K、OPTIMIZER、LR、EXPANSION_FACTOR 与主要 recipe 不变。相比更远的 factorized_topk，这个 probe仍沿同一 low-rank residual inheritance line，归因更干净，也更直接回答 soft-codebook coarse branch 本身是否值得继续。","summary":"执行一次严格 matched architecture probe：把当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 换成更简单的 lowrank_residual，其余 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 全部保持不变，用一轮干净对照判断 soft-codebook + two-stage 结构相对基础 low-rank residual 是否值得继续。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0172.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` with `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` fixed. Final reconstruction formula is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library, `{c_m}` is a static soft-codebook library, and `{b_i}` is a static residual dictionary; the gate only changes single-sample support weighting before top-k, not the exported decoder basis. This is `扩展兼容`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export it as one static trunk lookup plus one static codebook lookup plus one sparse weighted sum over a static residual library, so inference still reduces to finite weighted sums over fixed vector banks. At EF=2 its encoder selection cost is expected to remain within the `≤ 1.5×h×n` hard budget because it adds one gate scorer on top of the already-feasible `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` path while staying below the current two-stage mainline’s selector complexity. The single question is whether the soft-codebook coarse branch remains worthwhile with a cheaper gated single-stage selector, or whether the current two-stage refinement is still clearly necessary.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` is clearly worse than the two-stage mainline in both FVU and runtime metrics, discard this family and return to `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round.","If it is modestly worse in FVU but materially better in throughput or total runtime, keep it as a lower-complexity compatible reserve branch, but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy.","If it is unexpectedly close to the mainline at lower selector complexity, allow at most one later family-specific follow-up after the required return to the mainline."],"notes_to_memory":["Compatibility: `扩展兼容`. Export path is static trunk library + static soft-codebook library + static residual dictionary; gating affects only online selection, not decoder exportability.","This round is a strict matched architecture probe: keep `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` explicitly pinned, and change only `ARCHITECTURE`.","Evaluate with `tokens_per_sec`, total duration, and `final_total_tokens` alongside FVU, because LUTurbo cares about total runtime cost rather than FVU alone; small quality changes with noticeably worse runtime are negative."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"This obeys the single-variable rule by changing only `architecture` and explicitly pinning the current mainline recipe. Repeating `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` has already failed twice on policy-detection rather than science, so the highest-value remaining matched probe is a nearby soft-codebook selector variant that should still be budget-feasible and avoids the same controller edge case. `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` directly tests whether the coarse codebook branch is the real source of value while simplifying the residual selector relative to the current mainline.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` with the `K=128`, `EF=2`, `signum`, `LR=3.0e-3` mainline recipe fixed. This cleanly tests whether a softer codebook-plus-gated single-stage architecture is worth any continued attention under LUTurbo-compatible low-EF constraints.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0086.stdout.log:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` and `lowrank_residual_vq` both failed to pressure the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor, the most informative single matched architecture probe is `lowrank_jumprelu_residual`. It preserves the same low-rank static-library export path while collapsing the selector back to a single residual pass with thresholded support selection, which is more promising for LUTurbo's total online cost (`selection + coeffs + lookup + compensation`) than another multi-stage or routed variant. If it is still clearly weaker under the exact matched `K=128, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=2.0e-3, EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe, then this simpler low-rank single-stage family is not worth continuing in the current regime.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the round rule by changing exactly one primary variable: `architecture`. I kept the current mainline recipe fixed, explicitly pinned `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and chose a candidate that is LUTurbo-compatible and meaningfully simpler online than the current two-stage mainline. Risk: older low-K evidence for this family was weak, so this may just confirm that the simpler single-stage thresholded selector cannot retain enough quality at matched K128.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 86 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Judge this run as a family-worthiness test for a simpler low-rank single-stage thresholded selector that may reduce LUTurbo online selection and compensation cost; return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` is clearly weaker than the matched `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, discard it and resume mainline tuning on `lowrank_two_stage_residual` next round.","If `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` is unexpectedly competitive at matched K128, record it as a viable lower-online-complexity branch but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
