},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 89 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_residual` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Judge this run strictly as a family-worthiness test for the simplest low-rank single-stage residual decomposition; the core question is whether dropping the second residual stage can preserve enough quality to justify the lower expected online cost.","Return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome; do not chain another new-family probe immediately after this one."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_residual` is clearly weaker than the matched `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, discard it and resume mainline tuning on `lowrank_two_stage_residual` next round.","If `lowrank_residual` is unexpectedly competitive at matched K128, record it as a viable lower-cost branch but still return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round per probe policy."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
