research/history/logs/agent_round_0054.stdout.log:348:research/history/round_summaries/round_0042.json:104:    "description": "Stay on the active `gated` family and return to the `signum` anchor at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, with the same runtime knobs pinned, and change only the loss-side variable `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.0`. Judge this run by curve shape as well as terminal FVU: if dropping aux yields a smoother or lower full trajectory than the current `0.148156` anchor, then the stronger LR has made the auxiliary term unnecessary or harmful; if it regresses or destabilizes training, keep the default aux loss and move on to preprocess.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0054.stdout.log:352:research/history/round_summaries/round_0040.json:20:    "summary": "Stay on the same `gated` mainline and continue the learning-rate sweep with one adjacent confirmation step. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed, explicitly pin the reference aux/runtime knobs, and raise only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3`. Judge this round by full trajectory shape, not just terminal FVU: if early and mid training remain as smooth as Round 39 and the late descent goes lower than `0.148156`, then the LR optimum is still above the current anchor; if the curve gets noisier, flatter, or regresses, stop the LR branch and lock `2.0e-3` as the mainline setting.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0054.stdout.log:358:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 53 answered only the upward side of the re-opened LR question on the Hadamard-strengthened `gated` anchor: `LR=2.4e-3` stayed healthy but finished slightly worse than the current `0.142923` best, so the remaining single question is whether the new preprocess actually wants a smaller step size instead of a larger one. With `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, does lowering `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3` improve the full curve, or does `2.0e-3` remain the best shared mainline setting even after preprocess changed conditioning?","summary":"Stay on the active `gated` mainline and keep the family reference recipe fixed at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3` to complete the downward side of the LR localization around the current Hadamard anchor. Judge this run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if the lower LR yields a smoother mid/late descent and finishes below `0.142923`, then Hadamard shifted the preferred step size downward; if it is flatter or worse, lock `2.0e-3` as the operative mainline LR and stop the LR branch again.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `lr`, anchored on the current family reference point so it remains policy-clean. It also follows the requested mainline sequencing better than opening a new family or retuning K again: after the Hadamard-enabled anchor rejected the upward LR callback at `2.4e-3`, the most informative remaining single question is the symmetric downward callback before declaring the LR axis settled.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 53 showed that on the Hadamard-enabled `gated@128` anchor, raising `LR` to `2.4e-3` does not improve over `LR=2.0e-3`; the curve stayed healthy but the endpoint regressed slightly to `0.143811` versus the `0.142923` anchor.","Round 54 should isolate the remaining LR question on the same strengthened anchor by testing the downward callback to `LR=1.6e-3` at fixed `gated`, `K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=1.6e-3` improves the Hadamard-enabled `gated@128` curve or endpoint, adopt it as the new anchor or run one tight confirmation before revisiting other axes.","If `LR=1.6e-3` is also worse or uniformly slower, close the LR branch and keep `LR=2.0e-3` as the shared mainline recipe before considering any further family-local recipe work."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0040.stdout.log:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 39 improved the `gated` K128 anchor from `0.149936` to `0.148156` and the whole curve was better from start to finish while still improving late, so the LR branch has not saturated yet. The next single question is whether this gain continues one more small step upward: does `LR=2.4e-3` preserve the healthy curve shape and improve further over the new `2.0e-3` anchor, or does it begin to overdrive the recipe?","summary":"Stay on the same `gated` mainline and continue the learning-rate sweep with one adjacent confirmation step. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed, explicitly pin the reference aux/runtime knobs, and raise only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3`. Judge this round by full trajectory shape, not just terminal FVU: if early and mid training remain as smooth as Round 39 and the late descent goes lower than `0.148156`, then the LR optimum is still above the current anchor; if the curve gets noisier, flatter, or regresses, stop the LR branch and lock `2.0e-3` as the mainline setting.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This keeps the search on the active `gated` family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and changes exactly one core variable: `lr`. It also follows the stated policy to do one more nearby LR confirmation after a clean improvement, instead of prematurely switching axes or opening a new family. The main risk is overshooting into instability, but that is precisely the single question this round is meant to answer.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 39 established a new `gated@128` anchor at `LR=2.0e-3`, improving both endpoint and full-curve shape over the refreshed `1.6e-3` baseline.","Round 40 continues the same LR branch with one adjacent upward confirmation at `LR=2.4e-3` to determine whether the current gain was the start of a better regime or already near the stability limit."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated` at `LR=2.4e-3` improves again with a similarly healthy curve, consider one final tight confirmation near this region before moving on to optimizer.","If `gated` at `LR=2.4e-3` degrades or becomes visibly less stable, stop the LR branch and keep `LR=2.0e-3` as the gated mainline anchor before moving to the next recipe axis."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
