research/history/logs/agent_round_0217.stdout.log:189:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"K","value":"240"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"better_fvu_within_low_cost_region","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 来自单个静态向量库；在线侧只做单样本 top-k 选择与系数计算，导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 时仍是单库查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿，因此兼容性为直接兼容。r214-r216 已经连续证明在 EF=1 下沿 K 轴增加查表预算能稳定压低 <0.5x 区域的 FVU，而 r216 仍从 0.1635 改善到 0.1528，说明边际收益尚未耗尽；因此本轮继续在同一最短链路 family 上仅把 K 提到 240，目标是在总成本仍预计约 0.49x、继续留在 <0.5x 区域的前提下，把低开销区最佳 FVU 再向下压一截，并判断 topk@EF1 的收益是否开始真正接近平台。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 topk@EF1,K240 继续明显改善 FVU 且运行代价未恶化，则低开销区仍可再补一个贴边点。","如果 K240 的收益很小或训练时间明显变差，则说明 EF=1 下继续堆 K 已接近边际收益极限，后续应转向新的低成本 family。"],"notes_to_memory":["topk 目前是 <0.5x 区域最稳的直接兼容主线，且导出路径最简单，适合继续补低开销 Pareto 前沿。","r214-r216 已形成清晰趋势：在 EF=1 固定 encoder 成本下，增加 K 可以持续降低 FVU，因此当前最高信息量的单变量仍是 K 轴。","评估时必须同步比较 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时与 final_total_tokens，确认贴近 0.5x 边界后的额外查表预算是否仍值得。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"这轮选择 K=240 而不是直接上到 256，是为了尽量稳妥地继续留在 <0.5x 区域，同时测试靠近边界时的真实边际收益。风险是收益可能已开始明显变小，但这正是当前需要量化的关键信号。","summary":"继续使用直接兼容的 topk family，固定 EF=1、signum、LR=3e-3，把 K 提到 240，测试是否能在仍低于 0.5x 总成本的前提下，把低开销区最佳 FVU 从 0.1528 进一步压低。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0002.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"在 topk/signum 基线已建立后，本轮只下调学习率，检验基线曲线末段的更新噪声是否来自步长偏大；若是，则较小 LR 应该在不改 family/optimizer/K 的前提下带来更平滑的收敛并改善 FVU。","summary":"继续主线 topk，不开新 family，不换优化器，不动 K。本轮唯一主变量是学习率：从 8e-4 下调到 6e-4，回答“当前 signum+topk 基线是否因 LR 略大而限制了收敛质量”这个单一问题。","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"这是按主线顺序进行的单变量 LR 回调，归因清晰。风险是收益可能有限，但相比直接换优化器或改 K，这一轮更符合当前策略，也更容易结合训练曲线判断是过冲/震荡还是单纯欠训练。","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"6e-4"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 2 保持 topk/signum/K128/EF12 不变，只做 LR 回调以提高归因清晰度。","本轮重点看训练曲线是否更平滑、后段是否仍持续下降，而不只比较最终单点 FVU。","如果 6e-4 明显更稳且更优，后续可继续在 signum 下做小范围 LR 精调；如果更差或收敛更慢，再考虑换 optimizer。"],"next_hypotheses":["如果 6e-4 改善了后段收敛和最终 FVU，下一轮继续只调 LR 做更细化回调。","如果 6e-4 过小导致下降变慢或 FVU 变差，下一轮可回到 8e-4 附近并改为更高或中间 LR。","如果 signum 在两档 LR 下都已明显平台化，再按顺序只改 optimizer 做同 family 对比。"],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_round_0041.stdout.log:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 40 answered the LR question cleanly: `LR=2.4e-3` preserved a smooth curve but regressed slightly versus the new `2.0e-3` anchor, so the signum LR branch is now sufficiently localized around `2.0e-3`. The next single question in the prescribed order is therefore optimizer: with `ARCHITECTURE=gated, K=128, EF=12, LR=2.0e-3` fixed at the refreshed anchor recipe, does swapping `signum` to `adam` produce a healthier curve or competitive FVU, or does `gated` still clearly prefer `signum`?","summary":"Keep the active `gated` family and move to the optimizer axis now that the LR sweep has identified `2.0e-3` as the best current signum setting. Run `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.0e-3` with all reference aux/runtime knobs explicitly pinned, and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`. Judge the result by the whole trajectory, not just endpoint: if `adam` descends more cleanly or closes the gap at the stronger `2.0e-3` anchor, it earns exactly one LR callback next; if it is flatter, noisier, or clearly worse again, lock `signum` as the gated optimizer and stop the optimizer branch.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same mainline family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and changes exactly one core variable: `optimizer`. It follows the stated round order after the LR branch produced a modest win at `2.0e-3` and a slight regression at `2.4e-3`, which is enough evidence to stop spending more rounds on signum LR micro-tuning before checking optimizer. The main risk is that `adam` was already poor at `1.6e-3`, but that makes this a bounded confirmation rather than an open-ended sweep.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 40 slightly regressed from the `LR=2.0e-3` gated anchor while keeping a similarly smooth, still-improving curve, so the signum LR branch is localized enough to move on.","Round 41 switches the current `gated@128` anchor from `signum` to `adam` at fixed `LR=2.0e-3` to answer the next prescribed optimizer question under the updated mainline recipe rather than the older `1.6e-3` anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated+adam` at `LR=2.0e-3` is competitive or better with a healthy curve, run exactly one Adam LR callback next to test whether its usable range differs from signum.","If `gated+adam` at `LR=2.0e-3` is clearly worse again, keep `signum` as the gated optimizer and move on to the next recipe axis without further optimizer work."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
