research/history/logs/agent_round_0041.stdout.log:77:    "summary": "Stay on the same `gated` mainline and continue the learning-rate sweep with one adjacent confirmation step. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed, explicitly pin the reference aux/runtime knobs, and raise only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3`. Judge this round by full trajectory shape, not just terminal FVU: if early and mid training remain as smooth as Round 39 and the late descent goes lower than `0.148156`, then the LR optimum is still above the current anchor; if the curve gets noisier, flatter, or regresses, stop the LR branch and lock `2.0e-3` as the mainline setting.",
research/history/logs/agent_round_0041.stdout.log:86:research/history/results.tsv:41:r40_1774540147	1774540147	ok	archive	0.14828267693519592	128	gated	12				/root/sparsify-ascend/checkpoints/research_agent/round_0040/round0040_standard_1774539696_dp2_bs1_ga8_ef12_k128_20260326_234143	be1e129316e855c7d25054c3946730e6703eeb8b			Stay on the same `gated` mainline and continue the learning-rate sweep with one adjacent confirmation step. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed, explicitly pin the reference aux/runtime knobs, and raise only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3`. Judge this round by full trajectory shape, not just terminal FVU: if early and mid training remain as smooth as Round 39 and the late descent goes lower than `0.148156`, then the LR optimum is still above the current anchor; if the curve gets noisier, flatter, or regresses, stop the LR branch and lock `2.0e-3` as the mainline setting.	This keeps the search on the active `gated` family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and changes exactly one core variable: `lr`. It also follows the stated policy to do one more nearby LR confirmation after a clean improvement, instead of prematurely switching axes or opening a new family. The main risk is overshooting into instability, but that is precisely the single question this round is meant to answer.	/root/sparsify-ascend/research/history/logs/round0040_standard_1774539696.log
