research/history/logs/agent_action_0164.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"proxy","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual with K=128, EF=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3 unchanged. Final reconstruction remains x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j, where U(Vx) is a static low-rank trunk library, {c_m} is a static codebook library, and {b_i} is a static residual dictionary; only the stage-1/stage-2 budget split changes to a front-loaded 75/25 allocation. This is 扩展兼容 and exports cleanly to LUTurbo as trunk lookup + codebook lookup + two residual sparse lookups. Because this variant reuses the parent encoder modules, its selection-cost profile should stay matched to the mainline EF=2 point instead of introducing extra router/bucket scorer cost; the probe asks whether front-loading support budget improves low-EF reconstruction enough to justify future tuning.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If this probe is clearly worse in FVU or runtime, return directly to the mainline lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual recipe next round.","If it is competitive at similar runtime, the next single-variable follow-up is STAGE1_RATIO tuning within this asymmetric family rather than opening another new architecture family."],"notes_to_memory":["Compatibility: 扩展兼容. Export formula: x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j.","Probe choice rationale: matched to the current mainline formula class and likely budget-safe at EF=2, unlike routed/bucketed matched probes which add extra selector layers and risk policy rejection on selection cost.","This round is intentionally only an architecture probe; K=128, EF=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3 stay fixed."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"Upside is bounded because this family only changes a fixed stage split and was not strong historically at higher-EF regimes, so a null result is plausible. Still, it is the cleanest policy-safe matched probe that isolates architecture without confounding cost increases.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe with ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual and keep the mainline recipe otherwise unchanged. It preserves LUTurbo-exportable static-library reconstruction and mainline-like selection cost, so the result will answer whether asymmetric budget allocation is worth any continued attention in the current low-EF regime.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0171.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` with `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` fixed. Final reconstruction formula is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library, `{c_m}` is a static soft-codebook library, and `{b_i}` is a static residual dictionary. This is `扩展兼容`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export it as one static trunk lookup plus one static codebook lookup plus one sparse weighted sum over a static residual library, so inference remains a finite weighted sum over fixed vector banks. At EF=2 its encoder selection cost remains within the `≤ 1.5×h×n` hard budget and below the current two-stage soft-codebook mainline. The single question is whether removing the second residual refinement stage preserves enough quality and runtime efficiency to justify continued attention as a cheaper compatible branch, or whether the second stage is clearly necessary.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` is clearly worse than the two-stage mainline in both FVU and runtime metrics, close this parent branch for the current low-EF regime and return to `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round.","If it is modestly worse in FVU but materially better in throughput or total runtime, keep it as a cheaper compatible Pareto branch, but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy.","If it is unexpectedly very close to the mainline at lower selection cost, allow at most one later family-specific follow-up after the required return to the mainline."],"notes_to_memory":["Compatibility: `扩展兼容`. Export path is static trunk library + static soft-codebook library + static residual dictionary; no decoder basis depends on the input.","This round is a strict matched architecture probe: keep `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` explicitly pinned, and change only `ARCHITECTURE`.","Evaluate with `tokens_per_sec`, total duration, and `final_total_tokens` alongside FVU, because LUTurbo cares about total runtime cost rather than FVU alone; small quality gains with worse runtime are negative."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"This obeys the single-variable rule by changing only `architecture` and explicitly pinning the current mainline recipe. The previous attempt on this family was policy-rejected rather than scientifically resolved, so the highest-value action is to rerun the same matched probe cleanly instead of opening another new family. `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` is the strongest cheaper compatible parent and directly tests whether the second sparse stage is actually earning its extra cost in the current deployable low-EF regime.","summary":"Run one valid matched architecture probe on `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` while keeping the `K=128`, `EF=2`, `signum`, `LR=3.0e-3` mainline recipe fixed. This cleanly tests whether the cheaper one-stage soft-codebook parent is still worth continued attention under LUTurbo-compatible low-EF constraints.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0209.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"better_fvu_within_low_cost_region","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 b_i 来自单个静态向量库；导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 时仍是单样本 top-k 选择后的单库查表与加权求和，因此属于直接兼容。r208 已证明 topk 在 EF=1、K=64、total_cost=0.31x 下能显著优于此前 factorized_topk 低开销点，因此本轮保持 architecture=topk、EXPANSION_FACTOR=1、optimizer、LR 不变，只把 K 从 64 提到 96，沿 deployment 成本轴在 <0.5x 区域内换取更低 FVU。预计 deployment cost 由约 0.06x 升到约 0.09x，total_cost 约为 0.34x，仍稳居低开销区，同时有望明显改善当前 0.2583 的 FVU。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 K=96 在 EF=1 下明显改善 FVU 且仍保持较快训练吞吐，可继续单变量上探 K=128，寻找 <0.5x 内的更优 topk 前沿点。","如果 K=96 改善有限，则说明 EF=1 的字典容量已成为主瓶颈，下一步应转向新的低成本 family，而不是继续在 topk@EF1 上增加查表预算。"],"notes_to_memory":["topk@EF1 已经证明比同成本附近的 factorized_topk 更强，当前优先级应是在该 family 内补足 <0.5x 区域的 K 轴形状。","本轮只改 K，保持 encoder 成本不变，便于将收益或退化归因于 lookup 预算变化。"],"primary_variable":"k","self_review":"该提案严格遵守单变量原则，并直接面向 <0.5x 区域补点。主要风险是 K 增加带来训练时间上升，但相较于可能获得的 FVU 改善，这一代价在当前阶段可接受，且仍需结合 tokens_per_sec 一并评估。","summary":"固定 topk 的 EF=1、signum、LR=3e-3，只将 K 从 64 提升到 96，目标是在约 0.34x 总成本处获得一个比当前 0.31x 点更低 FVU 的新低开销 Pareto 候选。","touched_files":[]}
