research/history/logs/agent_action_0073.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 71 showed that `two_stage_residual` can benefit modestly from a higher `signum` learning rate, but Round 72 was policy-rejected because it tried to combine the optimizer test with that LR shift in a single `param_only` move. The next single mainline question remains the optimizer question, and it must be isolated cleanly from the archived reference recipe: with `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed, does switching `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam` produce a healthier curve or competitive final FVU, or does this family still clearly prefer `signum`?","summary":"Stay on the `two_stage_residual` mainline and answer the optimizer question without coupling it to the recent LR finding. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed at the current reference recipe, and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`. Judge this run by full curve shape against the signum reference, not just the endpoint: if `adam` is competitive and smooth, it earns one LR callback next; if it is clearly worse, keep `signum` and move on to the next recipe axis.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"mainline_improvement","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active mainline family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, uses an allowed `K`, and changes exactly one primary variable: `optimizer`. It directly fixes the Round 72 policy failure by reverting to the current mainline reference recipe instead of carrying forward the `LR=2.4e-3` adjustment into the optimizer test. The tradeoff is that this tests `adam` against the conservative anchor rather than the best observed signum LR, but that is the only policy-clean way to isolate the optimizer branch this round.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 72 was rejected on policy grounds because it coupled the optimizer change with the earlier LR adjustment; the rejection does not answer the optimizer-quality question itself.","Round 73 should isolate the optimizer axis cleanly by testing `adam` on the current `two_stage_residual` reference recipe at `K=128`, `EF=12`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, judging the whole curve rather than endpoint alone."],"next_hypotheses":["If `adam` is competitive with or better than the `signum` reference, give `adam` exactly one LR callback next within `two_stage_residual`.","If `adam` is clearly worse or noisier, keep `signum` as the settled optimizer and move to the loss or preprocess question next.","If `adam` is mixed, do not change K yet; use at most one optimizer-local LR probe only if the curve is plausibly salvageable."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0042.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 41 made the optimizer question clear: `gated+adam` is not merely slightly worse under the updated anchor, it shows the same pathological curve shape as before, with a strong mid-training blow-up and a much worse endpoint than `signum`. With the optimizer branch now effectively closed, the next single question in the prescribed order is loss: under the strengthened `gated` mainline recipe at `K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=2.0e-3`, is the default auxiliary loss actually helping, or does removing it improve the full training trajectory?","summary":"Stay on the active `gated` family and return to the `signum` anchor at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, with the same runtime knobs pinned, and change only the loss-side variable `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.0`. Judge this run by curve shape as well as terminal FVU: if dropping aux yields a smoother or lower full trajectory than the current `0.148156` anchor, then the stronger LR has made the auxiliary term unnecessary or harmful; if it regresses or destabilizes training, keep the default aux loss and move on to preprocess.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This keeps the search on the same family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and changes exactly one non-core variable after the optimizer branch was cleanly falsified twice. I am not spending another round on Adam LR because the updated `adam` trial was not borderline or merely mistuned; it repeated the same qualitative failure pattern and got worse at the stronger anchor. The main risk is that aux removal may have only a small effect, but it is now the next most policy-clean question before preprocess or K movement.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 41 strongly rejected `adam` for `gated` again: compared with the `signum` anchor it showed the same mid-curve blow-up pattern as the earlier `adam` trial and finished far worse, so the optimizer branch should be treated as closed.","Round 42 returns to the updated `gated+signum` anchor at `LR=2.0e-3` and isolates the loss axis by setting `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` to test whether the default auxiliary term is still helping under the stronger mainline recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` improves the curve or final FVU, keep loss-side tuning alive with at most one nearby confirmation on the same anchor.","If removing aux is worse or neutral, restore the default loss setting and move to the preprocess axis before any further K exploration."],"primary_variable":"loss"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0083.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`adam` at the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor failed catastrophically, so the optimizer question is now cleanly resolved in favor of `signum`. The next single question should move to the loss axis rather than K or another architecture change: dropping `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.0` tests whether the current mainline is being mildly over-regularized and whether a cleaner reconstruction objective improves the mid/late training curve under the settled `signum` recipe.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline and revert to the stable `signum` reference recipe, changing only `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.0` while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed. Judge the run by the full curve against the current anchor, especially whether removing the auxiliary loss improves or smooths late descent; if it regresses or destabilizes, restore the default loss and only then consider preprocess.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same family, explicitly keeps `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and changes exactly one primary variable on top of the settled `signum` anchor. The main risk is that the auxiliary term may still be helping latent usage even if its endpoint effect is small, but after the optimizer branch crashed the cleanest remaining mainline question is loss regularization rather than opening preprocess or moving K prematurely.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 83 closes the optimizer branch for `lowrank_two_stage_residual`: `adam` at the matched K128/EF12/LR=2.0e-3 anchor was a catastrophic failure, so `signum` remains the settled mainline optimizer.","This round opens the loss-axis check by testing `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` on the exact stable `signum` reference recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` regresses or destabilizes, restore `0.03125` and test exactly one preprocess variable next, such as `USE_HADAMARD=1` if still unexplored on this family.","If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` improves clearly, run exactly one clean confirmation on that loss setting before moving to preprocess or K.","Do not move K until the K128 mainline has a settled optimizer and at least one resolved loss/preprocess verdict."],"primary_variable":"loss"}
