research/history/logs/agent_action_0049.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 48 answered the `K=24` question positively: the strengthened `gated` recipe (`signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`) continued to transfer downward and now owns the `K=24` frontier with a materially better endpoint than the prior control. The next single question is where this benefit finally breaks under stronger support pressure: if we keep the same improved recipe fixed and reduce only `K` to `16`, does `gated` still preserve enough quality to remain the best low-cost point, or does the family advantage disappear once support becomes this tight?","summary":"Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `24` to `16` to test whether the current recipe improvement extends to the next allowed lower-cost support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes clearly below the current `K=16` control (`0.308437`), then `gated` has established a meaningful foothold in the low-K regime; if the curve degrades sharply or the endpoint lands near or above that control, treat `K=24` as the practical lower bound of the current gated recipe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `gated` family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `K`. It follows the current mainline logic because the baseline, LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess questions have already been resolved on this recipe, and the recent K sweep has now shown successful transfer at `K=96`, `K=64`, `K=32`, and `K=24`. The main risk is that `K=16` may fall outside the regime where the improved gating recipe remains effective, but that is exactly the highest-value remaining single-variable question for locating the LUTurbo cost-quality break point.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 48 established that the improved `gated` recipe transfers down to `K=24`: it beat the previous `K=24` control and now holds that frontier point.","Round 49 isolates the next deployment-relevant K question by testing whether the same recipe still wins at `K=16`, where LUTurbo online cost drops further but support pressure tightens again."],"next_hypotheses":["If improved `gated@16` clearly beats the existing `K=16` control with a healthy curve, continue once more to `K=8` under the same recipe to locate the next break point.","If `gated@16` fails to beat the control or shows clearly worse curve shape, stop the downward sweep and treat `K=24` as the lowest strong gated point under the current recipe."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0057.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 56 answered the loss question on the strengthened `gated` recipe cleanly enough: removing the auxiliary term finished essentially flat-to-worse (`0.142968` vs the `0.142923` anchor), so the mainline recipe remains `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. With LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess now all re-checked on the active family, the next single question in the prescribed order is back on the K axis: if we keep the finalized `gated` recipe fixed and reduce only `K` from `128` to `96`, does the lower-cost point still reproduce a healthy full training curve under the now-settled mainline recipe, or was the earlier `K=96` result partly specific to an intermediate recipe-validation phase?","summary":"Stay on the active `gated` family and hold the now-settled mainline recipe fixed at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `128` to `96` to refresh the first lower-cost deployment point under the finalized recipe. Judge this run by the whole trajectory, not just terminal FVU: if the curve remains smooth and lands near or below the current `gated@96` frontier (`0.160940`), then the strengthened recipe is stable enough to treat that lower-cost point as a reliable LUTurbo candidate; if it degrades materially, re-open the question of whether the prior K sweep depended on transient recipe-state rather than the settled mainline.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `k`. It also follows the required sequencing: the mainline recipe has now been re-localized on LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess, so returning to K is the clean next step. The main risk is spending a round on confirmation rather than frontier expansion, but after four consecutive non-improving recipe probes the most useful next question is whether the first lower-cost operating point is stable under the finalized recipe rather than only under the earlier sweep context.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 56 showed that on the Hadamard-enabled `gated@128` anchor, removing the auxiliary loss is neutral-to-slightly-worse (`0.142968` vs `0.142923`), so `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125` should remain part of the strengthened mainline recipe.","Round 57 returns to the K axis under the now-settled `gated` recipe by rechecking `K=96` at fixed `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and `EF=12`, with emphasis on whether the full curve remains clean and deployment-relevant."],"next_hypotheses":["If the refreshed `gated@96` run reproduces a healthy curve near or better than the existing `0.160940` point, treat the lower-cost frontier as stable and continue down the K ladder only if a further deployment question remains.","If `gated@96` degrades materially relative to its existing frontier point, investigate whether the earlier K sweep was less stable than it appeared before making more low-K conclusions."],"primary_variable":"k"}
