research/history/logs/agent_action_0105.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 104 promoted `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` to the EF=12 K128 frontier under the matched `signum`/`LR=2.0e-3` recipe, so the next single mainline question should be baseline stability rather than opening a new tuning branch immediately. Re-running the exact same `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual K=128 EXPANSION_FACTOR=12 OPTIMIZER=signum LR=2.0e-3` recipe will show whether Round 104 was a robust new anchor worth tuning from, and the decision should be based on the full curve shape, not only the final FVU.","summary":"Stay on the new `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and run a clean baseline confirmation with the exact reference recipe: `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, with no other recipe changes.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"confirm_baseline","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the required mainline sequence after a fresh architecture win: keep the new family, hold `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, optimizer, and LR fixed, and spend one round confirming that the improved result is repeatable before probing learning rate or optimizer. The tradeoff is delaying tuning by one round, but that is justified because recipe comparisons are only meaningful once the new baseline is shown to be stable.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 105 is a clean baseline confirmation for the newly promoted `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline at `K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`.","Judge this run by whole-curve repeatability versus Round 104, especially whether the early and mid training trajectory remains at least as strong as the promoted run rather than relying only on terminal FVU.","Do not open LR or optimizer tuning until this baseline has been confirmed or disproven cleanly."],"next_hypotheses":["If the baseline repeat matches or nearly matches Round 104 on curve shape and endpoint, open the within-family LR branch next, starting with one symmetric learning-rate probe.","If the repeat falls back materially or shows unstable curve shape, spend one more round resolving baseline robustness before tuning other recipe axes.","Do not change optimizer, loss, preprocess, or `K` until the new mainline baseline is localized."],"primary_variable":"baseline_confirmation"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0165.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"proxy","family_name":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on lowrank_soft_codebook_residual with K=128, EXPANSION_FACTOR=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3 unchanged. Final reconstruction formula is x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i b_i, where U(Vx) is a static low-rank trunk library, {c_m} is a static soft-codebook library, and {b_i} is a static residual dictionary. This is 扩展兼容: LUTurbo can export it as trunk lookup + codebook lookup + one residual sparse lookup, all over fixed vector libraries. The single question for this probe is whether removing the second residual refinement stage keeps enough reconstruction quality to justify the lower encoder selection cost and likely lower runtime in the low-EF regime.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If FVU regresses materially versus the mainline while runtime savings are small, return to lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual next round and stop probing nearby parents.","If runtime improves meaningfully at only modest FVU loss, keep lowrank_soft_codebook_residual as a cost-efficient compatible branch on the Pareto frontier, but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy."],"notes_to_memory":["Compatibility: 扩展兼容. Export path is static trunk library + static codebook library + static residual dictionary; no dynamic decoder weights.","This is a matched architecture probe that changes only ARCHITECTURE and stays safely within the known EF=2 selection-cost budget table.","Probe intent is architectural value judgment only: test whether the second sparse stage in the current mainline is worth its extra encoder cost/runtime under LUTurbo constraints."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"This probe is conservative because the family is already known and compatible, so upside is mostly in runtime-cost tradeoff rather than discovering a new best FVU. That makes it appropriate after the previous matched probe was policy-rejected: it isolates a single structural difference and should yield a clean comparable signal.","summary":"Run a single matched architecture probe with ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_soft_codebook_residual while keeping K=128, EXPANSION_FACTOR=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, and LR=3.0e-3 fixed. The probe tests whether the simpler one-stage soft-codebook parent is still worth continuing as a lower-cost LUTurbo-compatible branch relative to the current two-stage mainline.","touched_files":[]}
