research/history/logs/agent_action_0190.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"候选 probe family 的最终重构公式为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j；其中 low-rank trunk 库 U、静态 soft-codebook 库 {c_m}、以及两阶段 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都可静态导出，asymmetric two-stage 只改变 stage1/stage2 的预算分配，不改变最终 decode 仍是固定向量库上的有限加权和，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。本轮严格保持主线的 `K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3` 不变，只将 architecture 从 `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 改为 `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`，唯一问题是：在当前低 EF 可部署 regime 下，固定的非对称两阶段预算分配本身是否值得继续，还是它会在 FVU 与运行代价上都落后于当前对称两阶段 soft-codebook 主线。","summary":"插入 1 个 matched architecture probe：将当前主线 `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 替换为 `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`，其余 `K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3` 全部保持不变，用一轮干净对照判断非对称两阶段 soft-codebook 路线在当前可部署低成本 regime 下是否值得继续。","needs_sanity":false,"notes_to_memory":["`lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 满足 LUTurbo 导出契约，兼容性为扩展兼容：trunk 库 + soft-codebook 库 + 两阶段 residual 字典库。","本轮严格是 matched architecture probe：EF、K、optimizer、LR 与主线 recipe 全部固定，只改 architecture。","评估时必须同时检查 FVU、curve_start/mid/end、tokens_per_sec、总耗时与 final_total_tokens，避免把架构质量与运行时波动混淆。"],"next_hypotheses":["若 `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 明显落后于当前主线，则关闭 asymmetric two-stage soft-codebook 分支，下一轮回到 `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 主线。","若该 probe 的 FVU 接近主线且吞吐更好，可将其记录为较低系统成本的兼容备选，但下一轮仍回到主线。","若该 probe 意外优于当前主线，则说明非对称阶段预算在低 EF regime 值得继续，但本轮只做架构价值判断，不连续展开新 family。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"本轮遵守架构探针规则，只改一个主变量 architecture，并保持主线的 K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变。选择 `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 是为了在保留 LUTurbo 兼容的 trunk+codebook+two-stage 主干下，测试比 grouped/gated 更接近主线骨架的阶段预算改造是否本身值得继续。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0033.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The poor `gated+adam` result at `LR=1.6e-3` may reflect Adam being overdriven rather than fundamentally unsuitable, so one mandatory LR callback to `8e-4` with `ARCHITECTURE=gated, K=128, EF=12` asks only whether Adam becomes competitive when run in a more plausible range.","summary":"Round 32 rejected the optimizer swap at the matched LR: `gated+adam` finished far worse than the `signum` anchor, but that is not yet a fair read on Adam because `1.6e-3` is aggressive for this optimizer family. Per the prescribed order, the next single-variable question is the new-optimizer LR callback. Hold family, K, and EF fixed, keep optimizer as `adam`, and step LR down to `8e-4`. Read the whole trajectory: if the curve becomes much smoother and closes most of the gap, Adam was mostly mis-tuned; if it remains flat or unstable and still clearly trails `signum`, retire Adam for `gated` and move on to loss/preprocess choices.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This keeps the investigation on the same family and changes only LR relative to the immediately preceding Adam trial, which is the correct follow-up under the stated sequence. I am not touching K or opening a new family because the optimizer branch has not yet received its one LR callback.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"8e-4"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 33 is the single LR callback for the new gated+adam branch after the overdriven 1.6e-3 trial failed badly.","Use curve shape to decide whether Adam was simply mis-tuned; if 8e-4 is still clearly worse than gated+signum, retire Adam for this family."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated+adam` at `8e-4` is still clearly inferior, revert to the `signum` anchor and probe loss/preprocess next.","If `gated+adam` at `8e-4` becomes competitive with a healthier curve, keep Adam alive as an alternative recipe but avoid broad sweeps until it actually beats the signum anchor."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
