research/history/logs/agent_action_0048.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 47 answered the `K=32` question positively: the strengthened `gated` recipe (`signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`) did not collapse when support was cut in half again, and it now owns the `K=32` frontier with a materially better endpoint than the old control. The next single question is where that transfer finally breaks for LUTurbo-relevant cost reduction: if we keep the same improved recipe fixed and reduce only `K` to `24`, does `gated` still preserve enough quality to remain the best point at that lower online cost, or does the advantage disappear below `K=32`?","summary":"Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `32` to `24` to test whether the current recipe improvement extends to the next allowed lower-cost support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes clearly below the current `K=24` control (`0.272262`), then `gated` has established a meaningful mid-low-K foothold; if the curve degrades sharply or the endpoint lands near or above that control, treat `K=32` as the practical lower bound of the current gated recipe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `gated` family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `K`. It follows the current mainline logic because the baseline, LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess questions have already been resolved on this recipe, and the recent K sweep has now shown successful transfer at `K=96`, `K=64`, and `K=32`. The main risk is that `K=24` may fall outside the regime where the improved gating recipe remains effective, but that is exactly the highest-value remaining single-variable question for mapping the LUTurbo cost-quality boundary.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 47 established that the improved `gated` recipe transfers down to `K=32`: it beat the previous `K=32` control and now holds that frontier point.","Round 48 isolates the next deployment-relevant K question by testing whether the same recipe still wins at `K=24`, where LUTurbo online cost drops further but support pressure tightens again."],"next_hypotheses":["If improved `gated@24` clearly beats the existing `K=24` control with a healthy curve, continue once more to `K=16` under the same recipe to locate the next break point.","If `gated@24` fails to beat the control or shows clearly worse curve shape, stop the downward sweep and treat `K=32` as the lowest strong gated point under the current recipe."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0136.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"NUM_CODES","value":"32"}],"expected_win":"pareto_cost_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk 基库 U、soft codebook 库 {c_m}、两阶段 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都是静态可导出的固定向量库，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 时 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，已满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束。本轮只改一个主变量 NUM_CODES，把 codebook 容量下调到 32，回答一个问题：在保持主线 family 与 recipe 不变的前提下，是否能以更低的 code_router/codebook_matmul 选择成本和更低的 codebook_deploy 成本，维持接近当前 0.0581 的 FVU，从而形成更强的 LUTurbo 成本侧 Pareto 点。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 NUM_CODES=32 仅带来小幅 FVU 退化但明显降低 deploy/selection 成本，则继续细扫更小或中间的 NUM_CODES 以压 Pareto 前沿。","若 NUM_CODES=32 的 FVU 明显恶化，则说明当前 codebook 容量已接近必要下限，回到默认配置后优先改测 STAGE1_RATIO。","若 NUM_CODES=32 与 baseline 几乎等价且吞吐更好，则可把更小 codebook 视为新的 clean baseline，再继续主线 recipe 搜索。"],"notes_to_memory":["LUTurbo 导出形式未变，family 仍为扩展兼容。","r135 的 matched probe 说明去掉 soft codebook/coarse branch 会明显变差，因此主线继续保留两阶段 soft-codebook 结构。","本轮转向 NUM_CODES，是因为它同时影响 encoder 选择成本与部署 codebook 成本，比继续做无收益 recipe 更贴近 LUTurbo 真实目标。"],"primary_variable":"num_codes","self_review":"遵守单变量原则：family、EF、K、optimizer、LR 均固定，只改 NUM_CODES。该动作直接针对 LUTurbo 总成本中的 codebook 分支，且不触碰已证明重要的 family 主结构；风险是 codebook 容量过小会削弱 coarse branch 表达，因此必须同时检查 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时和 final_total_tokens。","summary":"回到主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual，在 EF=2、K=128、signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变的前提下，仅把 NUM_CODES 下调到 32，测试是否能用更小 codebook 获得更优的 cost-FVU 权衡。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0160.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"候选 probe family 的最终重构公式为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_i alpha_i b_i。其中 U(Vx) 可导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此最终重构仍是静态向量库上的有限加权和，可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 下 encoder selection_cost 约 0.62x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束，并且显著低于当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 的约 1.25x。r159 已经用 matched probe 说明去掉第二阶段 refinement 会从 0.0581 退化到约 0.0647，因此本轮只回答另一个互补的问题：在保持 K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 与主要 recipe 完全不变时，进一步去掉 soft-codebook coarse branch、退回到 lowrank_residual，是否仍值得继续，还是 soft-codebook 分支本身就是当前低 EF 可部署 regime 的必要结构增量。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 lowrank_residual 明显落后于当前主线，则说明 soft-codebook coarse branch 在当前低 EF regime 下仍然是必要结构，不应继续回退。","若 lowrank_residual 与当前主线接近且成本明显更低，则记录其为更激进低成本备选，但下一轮仍按要求回到主线。","若 lowrank_residual 意外优于当前主线，则说明当前主线 family 的 coarse branch 价值需要重新审视，但本轮仅做架构价值判断，不连续展开新 family。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_residual 满足 LUTurbo 导出契约，兼容性为扩展兼容。","本轮严格是 matched architecture probe：EF、K、optimizer、LR 与主要 recipe 全部固定，只改 architecture。","r159 已检验 two-stage 相对单阶段 soft-codebook 的结构价值；本轮补充检验 soft-codebook coarse branch 本身是否值得保留。","评估时必须同时检查 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时和 final_total_tokens，避免把架构质量与吞吐波动混淆。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"这轮遵守架构探针规则，只改一个主变量 architecture，并保持主线的 K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变。选择 lowrank_residual 而不是更远的 topk 或 factorized_topk，是因为它是当前主线去掉 soft-codebook 分支后的最近父节点，能最干净地隔离“soft-codebook coarse branch 本身是否值得”这个单一问题，同时提供显著更低 selection_cost 的直接对照。","summary":"插入一个严格匹配的架构探针：将当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 替换为 lowrank_residual，其余 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 全部保持不变，用一轮干净对照判断 soft-codebook coarse branch 在当前低成本 regime 下是否仍然值得保留。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0145.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.3e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk 基库 U、soft codebook 静态库 {c_m}、以及两阶段 residual 静态字典库 {b_i} 都可离线导出，因此可直接映射到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 时 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束。r144 已重新确认当前主线参考配方可稳定复现 0.0581 附近 FVU 且运行代价恢复正常，因此现在应按顺序回到单变量学习率轴，而不是继续做架构探针或过早切换 optimizer。本轮只回答一个问题：在保持 family、EF、K、optimizer 全不变的前提下，将 signum 的 LR 从 3.0e-3 小幅上调到 3.3e-3，是否能在不明显恶化 tokens_per_sec、总耗时和 final_total_tokens 的情况下，改善中后段收敛形状并把 FVU 压到 0.0581 以下。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 LR=3.3e-3 在曲线中后段与终点上优于 3.0e-3，且运行代价基本不变，则继续围绕 signum 做小步上探或复验。","若 LR=3.3e-3 与 baseline 基本等价或更差，则说明 3.0e-3 已接近当前 signum 最优点，后续应关闭 LR 轴并转向 optimizer 或成本轴。","若 LR=3.3e-3 只带来极小 FVU 变化但明显拖慢训练或拉长总时长，则将其视为负面 recipe 信号，不再继续上探。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 仍是当前兼容 frontier 上质量最强的可行主线，导出形式未变，继续属于扩展兼容。","r144 clean baseline 已重新确认主线参考配方稳定，因此后续 recipe 变化可以更可靠地归因到单变量本身。","学习率轴此前表明 2.4e-3 偏低、3.6e-3 未带来收益；3.3e-3 是对 3.0e-3 的最小上探，用于判断是否仍有轻微的 signum 步长余量。"],"primary_variable":"lr","self_review":"遵守单变量原则：只改 LR，family、EF、K、optimizer 与导出形式全部固定，不混入成本轴或 loss 轴变化。该动作符合当前推荐顺序，在 EF 成本可行且 clean baseline 已补齐后，先完成更细的 LR 局部搜索。风险是 3.3e-3 可能只会带来更激进但无收益的更新，因此评估时必须同时看完整曲线、tokens_per_sec、总耗时与 final_total_tokens，而不是只看最终 FVU。","summary":"继续围绕当前主线 family 推进，不开新 family；在 r144 已恢复 clean baseline 锚点后，本轮进入单变量 LR 微调，保持 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual、EF=2、K=128、signum 不变，只把 LR 从 3.0e-3 小幅上调到 3.3e-3，测试是否能改善中后段收敛并刷新当前可行 frontier。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0101.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Rounds 98 and 100 now make `LR=2.4e-3` the reproducible best signum setting for `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=128` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, so the next single mainline question is optimizer choice. Testing `OPTIMIZER=adam` on that settled recipe will show whether this family's remaining limitation is optimization dynamics rather than signum step size, and the decision should be based on the whole curve shape versus the archived signum anchor, not just the endpoint.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`, while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.4e-3` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the prescribed sequence after localizing the signum LR branch: same family, same `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` pinned, and exactly one primary variable changes. The main risk is that `adam` may want a different LR than `signum`, but this first optimizer comparison is still the correct isolated question before spending any round on an optimizer-local LR callback.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 101 opens the optimizer branch for the confirmed `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` K128 mainline after `signum` with `LR=2.4e-3` reproduced the best curve/endpoint.","Judge this run by the full trajectory against the settled signum anchor at `K=128`, `EF=12`, `LR=2.4e-3`, especially whether `adam` is smoother or more competitive through mid and late training rather than only comparing final FVU.","If `adam` is promising, it earns exactly one optimizer-local LR callback next; if it is clearly worse or unstable, keep `signum` and move on to loss or preprocess before touching `K`."],"next_hypotheses":["If `adam` is competitive with or better than the settled signum anchor, give `adam` exactly one LR callback next within `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`.","If `adam` is clearly worse or unstable at `LR=2.4e-3`, close the optimizer branch in favor of `signum` and move to one loss-side or preprocess question next.","Do not change `K` until the optimizer question has been resolved cleanly on this family."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0100.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 98 was the first signum learning-rate probe on `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` to beat the archived `LR=2.0e-3` K128 baseline, so the next single question is whether that higher step size is a real improvement or just run noise. Re-running the exact `LR=2.4e-3` recipe is still the cleanest test, and it should be judged by full-curve repeatability against the `LR=2.0e-3` and `LR=1.6e-3` runs rather than endpoint alone.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and rerun the promising higher-LR recipe with `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.4e-3`, changing no other recipe variable.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"confirm_baseline","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays within the same family, keeps `K` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and isolates the only unresolved mainline recipe axis: whether `LR=2.4e-3` is the right signum operating point. The tradeoff is spending one more round before opening the optimizer branch, but that is justified because optimizer comparisons should use a settled signum anchor rather than an unconfirmed one-off LR win.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 100 retries the unresolved `LR=2.4e-3` signum probe for `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=128` and `EF=12` after the previous confirmation attempt was policy-rejected rather than trained.","Judge this run by curve-shape repeatability versus the archived `LR=2.0e-3`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and Round 98 `LR=2.4e-3` runs, not by endpoint alone.","Only after resolving whether `LR=2.4e-3` is a stable signum anchor should the optimizer branch open on this family."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=2.4e-3` reproduces the stronger curve or endpoint, promote it to the operative signum mainline LR and test `OPTIMIZER=adam` next at that settled recipe.","If the `LR=2.4e-3` repeat falls back to a near-tie or worse than `LR=2.0e-3`, close the signum LR branch with `LR=2.0e-3` as the operative anchor and test `OPTIMIZER=adam` next there.","Do not change loss, preprocess, or `K` until the optimizer question has been isolated from the settled signum baseline."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0046.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 45 showed that the strengthened `gated` recipe (`signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`) transfers from `K=128` down to `K=96`, improving the prior `gated@96` result while keeping a smooth, still-improving curve. The next single question is whether that gain carries one more step down the cost ladder: if we hold the improved recipe fixed and reduce only `K` to `64`, can `gated` produce a clearly better lower-cost point than the old `K=64` result, or does the Hadamard benefit fade before this support level?","summary":"Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `96` to `64` to test whether the new recipe yields a stronger lower-cost deployment point at the next allowed support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if it stays smooth and finishes materially below the old `gated@64` control (`0.195828`), the improved recipe is genuinely useful beyond the `K=128` anchor; if it falls back toward the old curve, treat the current gain as mainly a high-K effect.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the current mainline family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `K`. It follows the prescribed order because the clean baseline, LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess questions have already been answered on this recipe, and Round 45 provided positive evidence that the improved recipe transfers at least to `K=96`. The main risk is that `K=64` may sit past the regime where Hadamard helps, but that is the highest-value remaining single-question probe for LUTurbo-relevant cost reduction.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Rounds 43-45 established a stronger `gated` mainline recipe: `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`, with reproducible improvement at `K=128` and successful transfer to `K=96`.","Round 46 isolates the next deployment-relevant K question by testing whether that improved recipe also lowers `gated@64` enough to strengthen the lower-cost part of the frontier."],"next_hypotheses":["If improved `gated@64` clearly beats the old `K=64` result with a healthy curve, continue once more to `K=32` under the same recipe to locate where the transfer breaks.","If `K=64` regresses toward the old control or shows weaker curve quality, stop the downward sweep and treat the improved recipe mainly as a `K=96/128` high-quality lane."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0207.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"quality_anchor_near_low_cost_boundary","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 b_i 来自单个静态向量库；在线只做单样本 top-k 选择，导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 时就是单库查表 + 加权求和，因此属于直接兼容。上一轮 factorized_topk 的 FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM 降本尝试被 policy 拦截，且当前 <0.5x 区域 FVU 明显受 scorer 容量限制；因此本轮固定 K=64、EF=2、optimizer、LR，仅把 architecture 从 factorized_topk 切到 topk，验证去掉低秩 scorer bottleneck 后，是否能在接近低开销边界的总成本下显著改善 FVU。预计 total_cost 约 0.56x，虽略高于 0.5x，但可作为最邻近的质量锚点，帮助判断 <0.5x 区域的主要瓶颈是否来自 factorization。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 topk@K64 相比 factorized_topk@K64 明显改善 FVU，则说明当前低开销区主要受低秩 scorer 限制，下一步应考虑在更接近 0.5x 的边界上探索更轻但非 factorized 的选择机制。","如果 topk@K64 提升有限，则说明问题主要来自预算本身而非 factorized scorer，下一步应转向新的低成本 family 或更激进的小库/小K 结构，而不是继续在 scorer 形态上纠缠。"],"notes_to_memory":["topk 是最干净的直接兼容单库基线，可用于判断 factorized_topk 在低成本区的 FVU 损失到底有多少来自 scorer factorization。","本轮只改 architecture，保持 K=64 这个当前最佳 <0.5x 邻近点的查表预算不变，便于归因。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"该提案严格满足单变量原则，并针对 r206 的 policy_reject 与当前开放假设做了最小转向。代价是总成本会从 0.44x 上升到约 0.56x，不能直接补 <0.5x 前沿，但它能高信息量地判断 factorized scorer 是否是低开销区 FVU 过差的主因。","summary":"切换到直接兼容的 topk family，固定 K=64、EF=2、signum、LR=3e-3，只改变 architecture，获得一个贴近低开销边界的质量锚点，用来判断去掉 factorized scorer 后 FVU 能提升多少。","touched_files":[]}
