research/history/logs/agent_action_0034.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With the `gated` mainline anchored back at `K=128, EF=12, optimizer=signum, lr=1.6e-3`, adding a small auxiliary sparsity-support loss via `auxk_alpha=0.03125` may improve training dynamics without changing the family or optimizer; this round asks only whether a light loss-shaping term reduces plateauing and yields a better full-curve profile than the plain baseline.","summary":"The optimizer branch already failed once (`adam` at the matched LR), and the follow-up Adam LR callback was policy-rejected, so the next valid mainline move is to return to the proven `signum` anchor and test one loss-side variable. Keep architecture, K, EF, optimizer, and LR fixed, and introduce a small `auxk_alpha` rather than a large perturbation. Evaluate the whole trajectory: if early progress is steadier and the run finishes at or below the current `0.149866`, loss shaping is worth keeping in play; if the curve is uniformly worse or distorts convergence, drop aux loss and preserve the plain gated recipe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same family, keeps EF fixed at 12, does not touch K, and changes exactly one main variable: `auxk_alpha`. It also respects the prescribed order by moving to a loss-side probe only after the basic LR and optimizer checks have not yielded an improvement.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 34 returns to the gated+signum anchor and begins the loss-side probe with a small aux term: AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125.","Judge this run by curve shape as well as endpoint; if aux loss does not help the trajectory or finish, drop it and avoid broad loss sweeps."],"next_hypotheses":["If `auxk_alpha=0.03125` improves the curve or endpoint, test one nearby aux setting to see whether the benefit is robust or over-tuned.","If the aux-loss run is clearly worse, revert to the plain gated anchor and only then consider a preprocess-side change before touching K."],"primary_variable":"loss"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0087.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `lowrank_residual_vq`, and `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` all failing to challenge the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor, the highest-value remaining matched architecture probe is `lowrank_gated_residual`. It keeps the same low-rank trunk and static-library export contract, but replaces the two-stage residual path with a single gated residual selector that is materially simpler for LUTurbo online execution. If this simpler low-rank gated family is still clearly weaker under the exact matched `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe, then the current evidence favors keeping the two-stage residual structure rather than continuing single-stage low-rank selector variants.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_gated_residual` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the matched architecture probe rule by changing only `architecture` and keeping the mainline `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe fixed. `lowrank_gated_residual` is a cleaner LUTurbo-aligned probe than another multi-stage or codebook-heavy family because it preserves static exportability while potentially lowering online selection and compensation complexity. The risk is that earlier low-K history for this family was weak, so this round may mainly confirm that simpler single-stage low-rank gating cannot retain the mainline quality at K128.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 87 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_gated_residual` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Judge this run strictly as a family-worthiness test for a simpler low-rank single-stage gated selector with potentially lower LUTurbo online cost; return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_residual` is clearly weaker than the matched `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, discard it and resume mainline tuning on `lowrank_two_stage_residual` next round.","If `lowrank_gated_residual` is unexpectedly competitive at matched K128, record it as a viable lower-complexity branch but still return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round per probe policy."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0037.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Because `gated` beat the matched `topk` control at `K=96`, the next single question is whether that advantage extends one more step down the support ladder; testing `ARCHITECTURE=gated, K=64, EF=12, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=1.6e-3` will show whether `gated` is broadly stronger across high-K frontier points or only wins near the very top end.","summary":"Round 36 changed the picture: `gated@96` is not just viable, it improved the frontier over the existing `topk@96` control, so the family has earned one more K-mapping round. Keep the anchored recipe fixed and step only `K` from `96` to `64`. This directly answers whether the `gated` advantage generalizes to the next adjacent frontier point. Read the full curve, not just the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes below the `topk@64` control (`0.1992608`), `gated` is a real high-K mainline candidate; if it drops back behind `topk`, then the family likely helps only in the upper-K regime.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the current family, keeps EF fixed at 12, and changes exactly one main variable: `K`. It follows the prescribed ordering because recipe tuning was already exhausted before K moves began, and `K=64` is the highest-value next probe after the successful `K=96` result.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 36 established that gated generalizes beyond K=128 by beating the matched topk control at K=96.","Round 37 should probe the next adjacent K point, gated@64 with the same signum/LR anchor, to test whether the advantage persists deeper into the frontier."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated@64` also beats `topk@64`, continue one more downward K probe because gated is shaping up as the stronger mainline family across multiple frontier points.","If `gated@64` falls back behind `topk@64`, treat gated as a high-K specialist and preserve it mainly for K>=96."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0143.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"候选 architecture 的最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 是单个静态字典库上的固定向量，alpha_i 为选出的稀疏系数，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为直接兼容。与当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 相比，factorized_topk 不再使用 trunk、soft codebook 或两阶段 refinement，而是用低秩 scorer 做单库稀疏选择，仍保持静态库有限加权和的部署形式；在 EF=2 下其 encoder selection_cost 约 0.38x h×n，显著低于当前主线的约 1.25x，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束，部署侧也只需单库 sparse lookup。本轮只回答一个 matched architecture probe 问题：在 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 完全不变时，这种更激进的低秩单库选择机制是否值得继续，还是它在当前低 EF regime 下会因表示能力不足而明显落后于现有 soft-codebook/two-stage 主线。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 factorized_topk 在大幅降低 selection_cost 的同时仅有有限 FVU 损失，则保留它作为低成本 LUTurbo 候选，但下一轮按策略回到主线 family。","若 factorized_topk 的 FVU 明显落后于 lowrank_residual 与 soft-codebook 系，则说明低秩单库 scorer 在当前 regime 下不值得继续，后续不再占用主线 probe 轮次。","若 factorized_topk 虽然更便宜但训练吞吐或总耗时没有优势，则将其视为负面系统信号，而不是仅凭低 selection_cost 继续推进。"],"notes_to_memory":["本轮是 Round 143 唯一允许的 matched architecture probe，严格保持 K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变，只改 architecture。","r141 与 r142 已表明去掉 second stage、再去掉 soft codebook 都会出现阶梯式质量退化，因此本轮改测一条更低成本但机制不同的直接兼容候选，判断非全字典低秩 scorer 是否值得保留。","评估时必须同时比较 FVU、selection_cost、deploy cost、tokens_per_sec、总耗时和 final_total_tokens，避免只按终点 SAE 指标判断架构价值。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"遵守单变量原则与本轮 probe 约束：只改 architecture，未联动 K、EF、optimizer、LR 或其他 recipe。选择 factorized_topk，是因为它在 EF=2 下 selection_cost 明显低于当前所有兼容 frontier 点，且属于直接兼容的单库静态表示，能直接回答“更激进的低秩单库选择机制是否值得继续”这一独立架构问题。风险是该 family 在旧的高 EF regime 曾明显偏弱，但当前低 EF 成本约束已发生 regime shift，这正是本轮 probe 的信息价值所在。","summary":"插入一个严格匹配的架构探针：把当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 换成更低成本、直接兼容的 factorized_topk，其余 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 全部保持不变，用一次干净对照判断低秩单库选择机制在当前 LUTurbo 成本约束下是否仍值得继续。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/round_summaries/round_0097.json:7:  "family_name": "lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0097.json:8:  "family_stage": "mainline",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0097.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Rounds 95 and 96 established a clean, repeatable `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` K128 baseline at `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, so the next single mainline question is the first within-family learning-rate probe. Lowering `LR` to `1.6e-3` tests whether this asymmetric soft-codebook two-stage recipe is currently slightly underdamped and could trade a bit of early speed for better late-stage descent and a lower terminal FVU; the decision should come from the whole curve shape versus the archived baseline, not just the last point.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0097.json:23:    "family_name": "lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0097.json:24:    "family_stage": "mainline",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0097.json:25:    "self_review": "This follows the prescribed sequence after a clean baseline repeat: stay on the same family, keep `K` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and change exactly one primary variable, `lr`. The main risk is that `1.6e-3` may simply slow a recipe that is already well tuned at `2.0e-3`, but that is the highest-value first LR-localization question before opening the optimizer branch.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0097.json:79:    "self_review": "This follows the prescribed sequence after a clean baseline repeat: stay on the same family, keep `K` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and change exactly one primary variable, `lr`. The main risk is that `1.6e-3` may simply slow a recipe that is already well tuned at `2.0e-3`, but that is the highest-value first LR-localization question before opening the optimizer branch.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0053.json:7:  "family_name": "gated",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0053.json:8:  "family_stage": "mainline",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0053.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Round 52 was policy-rejected because it tried to retune `LR` on `gated@4`, which implicitly changed both `lr` and `k` relative to the family reference recipe. The corrected next single question is therefore to retune `LR` exactly on the current `gated` anchor itself: with `ARCHITECTURE=gated, K=128, EF=12, OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed and the now-proven `USE_HADAMARD=1` preprocessing kept on, does raising `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3` improve the full curve further, or is `2.0e-3` still the best step size even after Hadamard strengthened conditioning?",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0053.json:20:    "summary": "Stay on the active `gated` mainline and return to the family reference point so the round passes single-variable policy cleanly. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, and change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if Hadamard has genuinely widened the stable step-size range, `2.4e-3` should preserve or improve early and mid descent and finish below the current `0.142923` anchor; if the curve gets flatter, noisier, or regresses, keep `2.0e-3` as the operative shared recipe and stop the LR branch again.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0053.json:23:    "family_name": "gated",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0053.json:24:    "family_stage": "mainline",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0053.json:25:    "self_review": "This fixes the Round 52 policy mistake by anchoring the LR question back on the current family reference recipe, so only one core axis changes. It also stays on the same family, respects `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and asks a useful recipe question after the K sweep rather than reopening another family. The main risk is that `2.4e-3` already regressed before Hadamard, but the preprocess improvement materially changed the anchor, so one clean LR retest on the strengthened recipe is justified before treating the step size as fully settled.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0053.json:79:      "Round 52 was policy-rejected because changing `LR` at `K=4` violated the param-only single-core-axis rule relative to the family reference recipe; future recipe retunes must be anchored back on the current reference point.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0053.json:104:    "description": "Stay on the active `gated` mainline and return to the family reference point so the round passes single-variable policy cleanly. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, and change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if Hadamard has genuinely widened the stable step-size range, `2.4e-3` should preserve or improve early and mid descent and finish below the current `0.142923` anchor; if the curve gets flatter, noisier, or regresses, keep `2.0e-3` as the operative shared recipe and stop the LR branch again.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0053.json:105:    "self_review": "This fixes the Round 52 policy mistake by anchoring the LR question back on the current family reference recipe, so only one core axis changes. It also stays on the same family, respects `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and asks a useful recipe question after the K sweep rather than reopening another family. The main risk is that `2.4e-3` already regressed before Hadamard, but the preprocess improvement materially changed the anchor, so one clean LR retest on the strengthened recipe is justified before treating the step size as fully settled.",
research/history/logs/agent_action_0148.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.6e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。其中 U(Vx) 可导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{c_m} 为静态 soft-codebook 库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此最终仍是多个静态向量库上的有限加权和，可映射到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 下 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束。r145 与 r147 在相同 family/K/EF/optimizer 下两次复现了 LR=3.3e-3 的更优终点 FVU=0.0579389，相比 3.0e-3 baseline 的 0.0581064 是稳定正信号；同时 r147 的更长耗时主要来自 tokens_per_sec 从约 166.5k 降到 66.6k，而 final_total_tokens 仍是 59,969,536，说明这次变慢更像运行时吞吐波动，不应提前终止 LR 轴。本轮只回答一个问题：在保持 family、EF、K、optimizer 与导出形式不变的前提下，把 signum 学习率从 3.3e-3 继续上探到 3.6e-3，是否还能延续中后段收敛改善并进一步压低 FVU，还是已经开始进入过冲区间。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 3.6e-3 终点继续优于 3.3e-3 且曲线未出现更早平台或震荡，则补一轮 clean repeat 确认新的 signum 主线 LR。","若 3.6e-3 与 3.3e-3 持平或更差，则关闭 signum LR 上探分支，把 3.3e-3 视为当前主线最优配方。","若 3.6e-3 明显过冲或训练曲线变差，则停止继续加大学习率，后续只在已确认的 3.3e-3 锚点上考虑其余单变量轴。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 的导出形式未变，仍属扩展兼容，可继续作为 LUTurbo 主线 family。","EF=2 继续满足 selection_cost 预算；K 保持 128，避免把部署查表成本变化与 LR 轴混杂。","r145 与 r147 已把 3.3e-3 从一次性噪声提升为可复现信号；r147 的慢速更像吞吐异常而非训练更长。","近期一些成本侧参数改动出现与 baseline 完全相同的终点与 token 轨迹，后续若再走成本轴，应先确认这些 override 在执行链路中的实际生效情况。"],"primary_variable":"lr","self_review":"遵守单变量原则：只改 LR，family、EF、K、optimizer 全部固定在当前主线参考配方。相比再开 optimizer 或 loss/preprocess 分支，这一步更符合当前主线推进要求，因为 3.3e-3 已给出稳定改善而其上界仍未确认。主要风险是 3.6e-3 只是更激进而不更好，因此评估时必须同时看完整曲线、tokens_per_sec、总耗时与 final_total_tokens，而不是只看最终 FVU。","summary":"继续围绕主线 family 推进，不开新 family；在 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual、EF=2、K=128、signum 固定的前提下，仅把 LR 从已复现改善的 3.3e-3 上调到 3.6e-3，判断 signum 上探是否还能进一步降低 FVU。","touched_files":[]}
