research/history/logs/agent_action_0174.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_grouped_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_grouped_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_grouped_residual` with `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` fixed. Final reconstruction formula is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library and `{b_i}` is a static residual dictionary; grouped competition changes only how residual support is selected, not the exported decoder basis. This is `扩展兼容`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export it as one static trunk lookup plus one sparse weighted sum over a static residual library, so inference remains a finite weighted sum over fixed vector banks. At EF=2 its encoder selection cost should remain within the `≤ 1.5×h×n` hard budget because it reuses the feasible `lowrank_residual` scorer stack and only constrains support selection. The single question is whether group-local residual competition is intrinsically worth keeping in the low-EF deployable regime, or whether even this cheaper selector simplification is clearly inferior to the current two-stage soft-codebook mainline.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_grouped_residual` is clearly worse than the two-stage mainline in both FVU and runtime metrics, discard grouped low-rank residual variants and return to `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round.","If it is modestly worse in FVU but materially better in throughput or total runtime, keep it as a lower-complexity compatible reserve branch, but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy.","If it is unexpectedly close to the mainline at lower selector complexity, allow at most one later family-specific follow-up after the required return to the mainline."],"notes_to_memory":["Compatibility: `扩展兼容`. Export path is static trunk library + static residual dictionary; grouped competition affects only online selection, not decoder exportability.","This round is a strict matched architecture probe: keep `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` explicitly pinned, and change only `ARCHITECTURE`.","Evaluate `tokens_per_sec`, total duration, and `final_total_tokens` alongside FVU, because LUTurbo cares about total runtime cost rather than FVU alone; a tiny quality change with slower runtime is negative."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"This obeys the single-variable rule by changing only `architecture` and explicitly pinning the current mainline recipe. After the recent soft-codebook selector probes did not pressure the mainline, the highest-value remaining budget-feasible matched probe is `lowrank_grouped_residual`: it avoids the repeated controller issue seen on `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual`, keeps the export contract simple, and tests whether local competition can buy meaningful runtime simplicity without collapsing quality in the current low-EF regime.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `lowrank_grouped_residual` with the `K=128`, `EF=2`, `signum`, `LR=3.0e-3` mainline recipe fixed. This cleanly tests whether a grouped low-rank single-stage residual architecture is worth any continued attention under LUTurbo-compatible low-EF constraints.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0186.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"TRUNK_RANK","value":"16"}],"expected_win":"pareto_improve","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j；其中 low-rank trunk 库 U、静态 soft-codebook 库 {c_m}、两阶段 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都可静态导出，因此可直接映射到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路，兼容性判断为扩展兼容。当前 family 在 EF=2 下 encoder selection_cost 仍满足 ≤1.5×h×n 硬约束。r133 把 `TRUNK_RANK` 降到 32 时几乎零损失复现了主线 FVU，r182-r184 继续压缩 `NUM_CODES` 也未改变终点，说明当前主线可能仍有明显结构冗余。本轮只回答一个问题：将 `TRUNK_RANK` 进一步下调到 16，是否仍能保持接近当前主线的训练曲线与终点 FVU，同时继续降低 trunk 相关的 encoder 选择成本与部署查表成本，从而推动兼容 Pareto 前沿向更低总成本移动。","summary":"继续围绕同一主线 family 推进，不开新 family；固定 `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual, K=128, EF=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3`，仅把 `TRUNK_RANK` 从已验证无损的 32 再降到 16，测试更激进的 trunk 压缩是否仍能维持当前 LUTurbo 可部署质量。","needs_sanity":false,"notes_to_memory":["family 与导出路径不变，`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 在 `TRUNK_RANK=16` 下仍是扩展兼容：trunk 库 + soft-codebook 库 + two-stage residual 字典库的有限加权和。","r133 表明 `TRUNK_RANK=32` 相对主线几乎无损，因此继续沿 trunk 容量轴下探比重复未增益的 `NUM_CODES` 压缩更有信息价值。","评估本轮必须同时比较 curve_start/mid/end、tokens_per_sec、总耗时与 final_total_tokens，确认任何收益来自真实成本下降而非运行时漂移。"],"next_hypotheses":["若 `TRUNK_RANK=16` 仍接近当前主线 FVU 且吞吐不恶化，可将更低 rank 视为新的低成本主线，并考虑继续下探或做一次 clean baseline 复验。","若 `TRUNK_RANK=16` 明显退化，则说明 trunk 容量下限更接近 32，下一轮回到 `TRUNK_RANK=32` 并转向 `NUM_CODES` 或其他单一成本轴。","若终点接近但吞吐显著变差，则把更低 trunk rank 视为负面系统信号，而不是仅凭 FVU 保留。"],"primary_variable":"trunk_rank","self_review":"本轮严格遵守单变量原则：family、EF、K、optimizer、LR 全部固定，只推进 `TRUNK_RANK` 这一直接作用于 encoder 选择成本和部署 trunk 成本的主变量。相比继续尝试在 policy 上有风险的 optimizer 分支，这一步更稳、更可归因，也更贴近 LUTurbo 的真实总成本目标。","touched_files":[]}
