research/history/logs/agent_action_0104.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After five non-improving mainline rounds, the single highest-value matched architecture probe is the direct parent family `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`. It preserves the same LUTurbo-compatible static-library export form as the current `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline, but removes the hand-set asymmetric stage allocation, so this round answers one clean question: is the asymmetry itself actually carrying the current K128/EF12 result, or would the simpler symmetric two-stage soft-codebook backbone be competitive enough to justify future follow-up instead.","summary":"Use the one allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, keeping `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed and changing only `ARCHITECTURE`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 104 probe rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping the current mainline reference recipe fixed. It is a stronger probe than opening a more exotic branch because it isolates whether the current win comes from the soft-codebook two-stage backbone itself or specifically from the asymmetric budget choice, and it stays aligned with LUTurbo deployment constraints.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 104 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` against the exact `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 mainline reference.","Judge this probe by full-curve shape as well as final FVU, especially whether the simpler symmetric two-stage soft-codebook backbone is competitive enough that the current asymmetric split may be unnecessary.","Return to the `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome; this probe is only a yes/no family-worthiness check."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` is clearly weaker than the matched asymmetric mainline, treat the asymmetric stage allocation as a meaningful ingredient and return to mainline recipe work next round.","If `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` is competitive on curve shape or endpoint, record it as a simpler reserve family but still return to the asymmetric mainline next round per probe policy.","Do not open a second architecture probe next round; the next step should go back to mainline recipe clarification."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
