research/history/round_summaries/round_0085.json:20:    "summary": "Run one matched architecture probe by switching only `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_residual_vq` while keeping the mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the baseline loss/runtime settings unchanged. Judge the probe by the full curve, not just endpoint FVU: if `lowrank_residual_vq` stays smooth and materially pressures the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, it remains worth keeping in reserve; if it is clearly weaker or less stable, close the family-worthiness question and return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0085.json:23:    "family_name": "lowrank_residual_vq",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0085.json:24:    "family_stage": "prototype",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0085.json:25:    "self_review": "This obeys the Round 85 matched-probe rule: one probe only, one main variable only, and `K`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` remain fixed. I chose `lowrank_residual_vq` because it is a genuinely different but still LUTurbo-compatible decomposition pattern with stronger prior signal than simpler selector-only families. The main risk is that hard assignment raises brittleness and may underperform on curve smoothness even if early descent looks acceptable, which is why the full trajectory matters more than the final scalar alone.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0085.json:56:      "Interpret this as a family-worthiness screen only: because hard residual-VQ can add discrete-selection brittleness, only a clear and stable quality advantage justifies future follow-up."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0085.json:80:    "description": "Run one matched architecture probe by switching only `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_residual_vq` while keeping the mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the baseline loss/runtime settings unchanged. Judge the probe by the full curve, not just endpoint FVU: if `lowrank_residual_vq` stays smooth and materially pressures the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, it remains worth keeping in reserve; if it is clearly weaker or less stable, close the family-worthiness question and return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0085.json:81:    "self_review": "This obeys the Round 85 matched-probe rule: one probe only, one main variable only, and `K`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` remain fixed. I chose `lowrank_residual_vq` because it is a genuinely different but still LUTurbo-compatible decomposition pattern with stronger prior signal than simpler selector-only families. The main risk is that hard assignment raises brittleness and may underperform on curve smoothness even if early descent looks acceptable, which is why the full trajectory matters more than the final scalar alone.",
research/history/logs/agent_action_0179.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"proxy","family_name":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` under the unchanged mainline recipe (`K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3.0e-3`). Final reconstruction is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk and the JumpReLU selector only changes which residual dictionary atoms `b_i` are activated and their coefficients. This is `扩展兼容`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export the trunk factors and residual dictionary as static vector libraries, then execute `trunk lookup + thresholded sparse selection + weighted lookup-sum` online. The probe asks one question only: in the low-EF feasible regime, does learned thresholding provide a better architecture tradeoff than the current soft-codebook two-stage mainline, or should this family be ruled out. Encoder selection cost should stay in the feasible band at `EF=2`, so this should produce a real signal instead of a policy reject.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["Return to the mainline `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round and tune exactly one cost knob such as `TRUNK_RANK`, `NUM_CODES`, or `STAGE1_RATIO`.","If `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` underperforms the mainline on FVU or shows materially worse `tokens_per_sec`/runtime without compensating benefit, mark the family as not worth continuing in the low-cost regime."],"notes_to_memory":["`lowrank_jumprelu_residual` is LUTurbo `扩展兼容`: decode remains a finite weighted sum over a static low-rank trunk plus a static residual dictionary; JumpReLU only changes selector-side activation sparsity.","This matched probe stays inside the likely feasible encoder-cost regime and is more informative than another routed/bucketed-style over-budget probe.","When scoring the run, inspect `tokens_per_sec`, wall-clock time, and `final_total_tokens` together with FVU; a tiny quality gain with slower training is a negative signal."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"Single-variable discipline is preserved: only `ARCHITECTURE` changes while `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, and `LR` remain fixed to the mainline recipe. This probe avoids another likely budget rejection and tests a remaining compatible architecture that can still deliver a clean go/no-go answer for the low-EF frontier.","summary":"Probe `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` as the one matched architecture change. It is LUTurbo-exportable (`扩展兼容`) through a static low-rank trunk plus static residual dictionary, and it should give a real low-cost signal on whether learned thresholding is worth continuing versus the current soft-codebook two-stage mainline.","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0135.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"architecture_value_signal","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"matched_probe","hypothesis":"候选架构的最终重构公式为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_i alpha_i b_i。low-rank trunk 基库 U 与 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都是静态可导出的固定向量库，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 matched architecture probe 严格保持主线的 K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变，只把 architecture 改为更简单的 lowrank_residual，用来回答一个问题：在当前低 EF 可行区间内，soft codebook coarse branch 是否仍然必要，还是 low-rank trunk + 单阶段 residual 已足够形成更优的成本/时延权衡。该架构在 EF=2 下 selection_cost 约 0.62x h×n，低于当前主线的 1.25x，若 FVU 没有明显恶化且运行更快，则值得作为低成本备选继续保留。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 lowrank_residual 的 FVU 接近主线且吞吐更好，则说明当前 EF=2 下 coarse codebook 的边际收益有限，下一轮回到主线后应重新审视更简单 family 的成本优势。","若 lowrank_residual 明显劣于主线，则说明 soft codebook coarse branch 在低 EF 下仍然必要，下一轮回到 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 继续做成本轴微调。","若 lowrank_residual 介于主线与 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 之间且更快，可将其记为低成本备用点，但不替代当前最佳 FVU 主线。"],"notes_to_memory":["本轮仍是单次 matched architecture probe，严格保持 K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变，只改 architecture。","lowrank_residual 为扩展兼容 family，且在 EF=2 下 selection_cost 明显低于当前两阶段主线，适合回答 coarse codebook 是否必要。","r134 的 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual probe 被 policy_reject，因此本轮改用另一个已知兼容且更低成本的父节点进行架构价值判断。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"遵守本轮架构探针约束，没有联动改 recipe。选择 lowrank_residual 而非继续重复被拒的 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual probe，可以更直接测试 soft codebook 分支本身的必要性；风险是该 family 可能在 K=128 下 FVU 明显偏弱，但这正是探针需要确认的信号。","summary":"做一个新的 matched architecture probe：仅把 architecture 改为 lowrank_residual，其余保持 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变，测量去掉 soft codebook 与第二阶段 refinement 后，这个更低成本父节点是否还值得继续。","touched_files":[]}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0091.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`whitened_lowrank_residual` failed catastrophically at the matched K128 anchor, so the next matched architecture probe should avoid more whitening-style conditioning and instead test a different single-stage low-rank selector family. The most informative remaining probe is `lowrank_factorized_residual`: it preserves the low-rank trunk and static-library weighted-sum export path, but replaces the plain residual scorer with a factorized scorer. This answers one clean question: can a more structured single-stage selector recover enough of the two-stage mainline's quality to be worth continuing, or is the second residual stage itself the essential ingredient. If `lowrank_factorized_residual` is still clearly weaker under the exact matched `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe, then the remaining single-stage low-rank selector variants are likely not worth further follow-up in the current regime.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_factorized_residual` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the round policy by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping the mainline `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe fixed. I am explicitly avoiding `lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual` because with the current batch-size-1 regime it collapses to ordinary top-k behavior and would not be an informative matched probe. The main risk is that `lowrank_factorized_residual` may add selector complexity without helping quality or LUTurbo online cost, so this should be judged strictly as a yes/no family-worthiness test before returning to the mainline.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_factorized_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 91 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_factorized_residual` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Avoid `lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual` in this batch-size-1 regime because its adaptive budget path degenerates to ordinary top-k and is not a meaningful architecture probe.","Judge this run strictly as a family-worthiness test for a structured single-stage low-rank selector; return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_factorized_residual` is clearly weaker than the matched `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, treat the remaining single-stage low-rank selector variants as low priority and resume mainline tuning next round.","If `lowrank_factorized_residual` is unexpectedly competitive at matched K128, record it as a structured single-stage comparison point but still return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round per probe policy."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0028.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With the `topk` mainline saturated for five rounds, the highest-value matched architecture probe is a directly compatible near-neighbor that changes support formation without changing the exported reconstruction form. `whitened_topk` keeps the same `K=128` sparse weighted-sum decoder contract as `topk` but adds input preconditioning before top-k competition, so this round asks one clean question: does that architectural change alone produce a meaningfully better curve or enough promise to justify follow-up work.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `whitened_topk`. Keep `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and the current stable non-compiled runtime/aux recipe fixed, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `topk` to `whitened_topk` to test whether this directly export-compatible variant is worth continuing as a family.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"whitened_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the Round 28 rule for a single matched architecture probe, changes exactly one primary variable (`architecture`), and chooses a candidate that remains close to LUTurbo's static-vector weighted-sum deployment contract. The main risk is that the preconditioning may add training complexity without improving reconstruction, but that is precisely the yes/no family-worthiness question this probe is meant to answer before returning to the mainline next round.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"whitened_topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 28 inserts exactly one matched architecture probe after five consecutive non-improving topk rounds; the probe must be judged as a family-worthiness test, not as a new mainline pivot.","`whitened_topk` is directly compatible with LUTurbo's deployment form because the final reconstruction remains a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library with fixed `K`; the architectural change is confined to encoder-side preconditioning and selection.","Judge this probe by full curve shape plus final FVU relative to the stabilized K128 topk control: if it is clearly worse or unstable, drop the family and return to topk; if it is competitive or better, it earns at most one follow-up slot later, but the immediate next round should still return to the topk mainline."],"next_hypotheses":["If `whitened_topk` is clearly worse than the stabilized `topk` control, archive it immediately and return to mainline topk recipe work next round.","If `whitened_topk` is roughly competitive with a smoother or still-descending curve, record it as a promising probe result but still return to the topk mainline next round per policy.","If `whitened_topk` beats the matched topk control, schedule exactly one later follow-up on the same family after the mandated return to the mainline."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0038.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The `gated` mainline has already shown smooth, still-improving curves at `K=128`, `K=96`, and `K=64`, but Round 38 should first fill the missing clean-baseline step in the prescribed order. Re-running the exact `gated` reference recipe with all reference aux/runtime knobs explicitly pinned answers one question only: does the true anchor still reproduce a clean curve under the current stack before we spend another round on lower `K` or renewed recipe tuning?","summary":"Run a clean control on the current `gated` mainline reference recipe. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=1.6e-3`, and explicitly lock the known reference aux/runtime settings so the next comparison is grounded in a fresh, fully specified anchor curve. Judge this run by the whole trajectory, not just terminal FVU: recent `gated` runs at `K=96` and `K=64` were still improving late, so we need a refreshed `K=128` control before deciding whether to continue down the K ladder or revisit LR.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `gated` family, respects the EF=12 constraint, and avoids opening a new branch. It also repairs the sequencing gap in the current mainline by adding the missing clean baseline before any further K move. The main risk is that it may not improve the frontier numerically, but right now the more important value is a fresh, comparable anchor curve for the next decision.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 38 backfills the missing clean-baseline step for the active `gated` mainline with the exact reference recipe explicitly pinned at `K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=1.6e-3`.","Recent `gated` K sweeps at `K=96` and `K=64` both had smooth, still-improving curves, so a refreshed `K=128` control is needed before interpreting any further K descent or LR changes."],"next_hypotheses":["If the clean `gated@128` control reproduces the expected anchor with a healthy late curve, resume the K ladder and test `K=32` next to locate where `gated` stops beating `topk`.","If the refreshed baseline comes in materially different from the recorded anchor, treat baseline reproducibility as the immediate issue and avoid drawing more family-quality conclusions from the recent K sweep alone."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history/logs/agent_action_0041.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 40 answered the LR question cleanly: `LR=2.4e-3` preserved a smooth curve but regressed slightly versus the new `2.0e-3` anchor, so the signum LR branch is now sufficiently localized around `2.0e-3`. The next single question in the prescribed order is therefore optimizer: with `ARCHITECTURE=gated, K=128, EF=12, LR=2.0e-3` fixed at the refreshed anchor recipe, does swapping `signum` to `adam` produce a healthier curve or competitive FVU, or does `gated` still clearly prefer `signum`?","summary":"Keep the active `gated` family and move to the optimizer axis now that the LR sweep has identified `2.0e-3` as the best current signum setting. Run `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.0e-3` with all reference aux/runtime knobs explicitly pinned, and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`. Judge the result by the whole trajectory, not just endpoint: if `adam` descends more cleanly or closes the gap at the stronger `2.0e-3` anchor, it earns exactly one LR callback next; if it is flatter, noisier, or clearly worse again, lock `signum` as the gated optimizer and stop the optimizer branch.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same mainline family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and changes exactly one core variable: `optimizer`. It follows the stated round order after the LR branch produced a modest win at `2.0e-3` and a slight regression at `2.4e-3`, which is enough evidence to stop spending more rounds on signum LR micro-tuning before checking optimizer. The main risk is that `adam` was already poor at `1.6e-3`, but that makes this a bounded confirmation rather than an open-ended sweep.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 40 slightly regressed from the `LR=2.0e-3` gated anchor while keeping a similarly smooth, still-improving curve, so the signum LR branch is localized enough to move on.","Round 41 switches the current `gated@128` anchor from `signum` to `adam` at fixed `LR=2.0e-3` to answer the next prescribed optimizer question under the updated mainline recipe rather than the older `1.6e-3` anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated+adam` at `LR=2.0e-3` is competitive or better with a healthy curve, run exactly one Adam LR callback next to test whether its usable range differs from signum.","If `gated+adam` at `LR=2.0e-3` is clearly worse again, keep `signum` as the gated optimizer and move on to the next recipe axis without further optimizer work."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
