research/history/round_summaries/round_0100.json:25:    "self_review": "This stays within the same family, keeps `K` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and isolates the only unresolved mainline recipe axis: whether `LR=2.4e-3` is the right signum operating point. The tradeoff is spending one more round before opening the optimizer branch, but that is justified because optimizer comparisons should use a settled signum anchor rather than an unconfirmed one-off LR win.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0100.json:53:      "Only after resolving whether `LR=2.4e-3` is a stable signum anchor should the optimizer branch open on this family."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0100.json:79:    "self_review": "This stays within the same family, keeps `K` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and isolates the only unresolved mainline recipe axis: whether `LR=2.4e-3` is the right signum operating point. The tradeoff is spending one more round before opening the optimizer branch, but that is justified because optimizer comparisons should use a settled signum anchor rather than an unconfirmed one-off LR win.",
research/history/logs/agent_action_0172.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` with `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` fixed. Final reconstruction formula is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library, `{c_m}` is a static soft-codebook library, and `{b_i}` is a static residual dictionary; the gate only changes single-sample support weighting before top-k, not the exported decoder basis. This is `扩展兼容`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export it as one static trunk lookup plus one static codebook lookup plus one sparse weighted sum over a static residual library, so inference still reduces to finite weighted sums over fixed vector banks. At EF=2 its encoder selection cost is expected to remain within the `≤ 1.5×h×n` hard budget because it adds one gate scorer on top of the already-feasible `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` path while staying below the current two-stage mainline’s selector complexity. The single question is whether the soft-codebook coarse branch remains worthwhile with a cheaper gated single-stage selector, or whether the current two-stage refinement is still clearly necessary.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` is clearly worse than the two-stage mainline in both FVU and runtime metrics, discard this family and return to `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round.","If it is modestly worse in FVU but materially better in throughput or total runtime, keep it as a lower-complexity compatible reserve branch, but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy.","If it is unexpectedly close to the mainline at lower selector complexity, allow at most one later family-specific follow-up after the required return to the mainline."],"notes_to_memory":["Compatibility: `扩展兼容`. Export path is static trunk library + static soft-codebook library + static residual dictionary; gating affects only online selection, not decoder exportability.","This round is a strict matched architecture probe: keep `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` explicitly pinned, and change only `ARCHITECTURE`.","Evaluate with `tokens_per_sec`, total duration, and `final_total_tokens` alongside FVU, because LUTurbo cares about total runtime cost rather than FVU alone; small quality changes with noticeably worse runtime are negative."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"This obeys the single-variable rule by changing only `architecture` and explicitly pinning the current mainline recipe. Repeating `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` has already failed twice on policy-detection rather than science, so the highest-value remaining matched probe is a nearby soft-codebook selector variant that should still be budget-feasible and avoids the same controller edge case. `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` directly tests whether the coarse codebook branch is the real source of value while simplifying the residual selector relative to the current mainline.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` with the `K=128`, `EF=2`, `signum`, `LR=3.0e-3` mainline recipe fixed. This cleanly tests whether a softer codebook-plus-gated single-stage architecture is worth any continued attention under LUTurbo-compatible low-EF constraints.","touched_files":[]}
