research/history/logs/agent_action_0200.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe under the fixed mainline recipe. Final reconstruction formula is x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j, where the only structural change versus the current mainline is a front-loaded stage split with stage1_k≈0.75K and stage2_k≈0.25K. This is LUTurbo 扩展兼容 because the trunk term U(Vx), soft-codebook branch Σ_m pi_m c_m, and both residual sparse branches all decode from static vector libraries, so inference still exports to LUTurbo/Lottable as static lookup tables plus weighted sums plus optional residual compensation. The probe asks one question only: at K=128, EF=2, signum, LR=3.0e-3, is the asymmetric two-stage budget intrinsically better than the symmetric split enough to justify keeping this family alive?","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["After this probe, return to the lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual mainline next round.","If asymmetric two-stage again fails to beat the symmetric parent in the EF=2 feasible regime, mark this family not worth continuing."],"notes_to_memory":["Round 199 was policy-rejected because the action was framed as param_only; this retry keeps the exact same scientific hypothesis but uses the correct architecture-only probe schema.","Compatibility label: 扩展兼容. Export path remains low-rank trunk library + soft codebook library + residual dictionary library.","Feasibility check: this family stays within the 1.5x encoder selection-cost cap at EF=2, unlike routed/bucketed two-stage soft-codebook variants which would be over budget in the matched setting.","Because recent rounds have become slower, this probe should be judged on tokens_per_sec, total runtime, and final_total_tokens in addition to FVU; a tiny FVU gain with worse throughput is a negative signal."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"This is a strict one-variable matched architecture probe: K, EXPANSION_FACTOR, OPTIMIZER, and LR remain fixed. I am reusing the same candidate as the rejected Round 199 attempt because the scientific question was valid and the rejection appears procedural rather than scientific. Routed and bucketed two-stage soft-codebook variants are intentionally excluded because their EF=2 encoder selection cost exceeds the hard budget and would likely be blocked again.","summary":"Retry the matched architecture probe with ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual under the unchanged mainline recipe. It is LUTurbo 扩展兼容, preserves the same deployable formula class as the current parent, and is the nearest feasible architecture perturbation for testing whether asymmetric stage allocation is worth continuing.","touched_files":[]}
