research/history/round_summaries/round_0106.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Rounds 104 and 105 established a clean, repeatable `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` K128 baseline at `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, so the next single mainline question is the first within-family learning-rate probe. Lowering `LR` to `1.6e-3` tests whether this two-stage soft-codebook recipe is slightly underdamped and could trade a bit of early speed for better late-stage descent and a lower terminal FVU; the decision should come from the whole curve shape versus the archived baseline, not just the last point.",
