research/history/round_summaries/round_0080.json:25:    "self_review": "This stays on the same family, keeps EF pinned to 12, and changes exactly one primary variable: `lr`. The tradeoff is that a lower LR may simply undertrain a recipe that is already stable at `2.0e-3`, but that is the cleanest first LR-localization question after the baseline repeat and is safer than opening the optimizer branch too early.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0080.json:56:      "Interpretation should prioritize curve shape: if `1.6e-3` is smoother but clearly slower with no late recovery, treat the family as preferring the original or higher LR rather than continuing downward."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0080.json:59:      "If `LR=1.6e-3` underperforms or converges too slowly, test only `LR=2.4e-3` next on the same family and anchor recipe.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0080.json:82:    "self_review": "This stays on the same family, keeps EF pinned to 12, and changes exactly one primary variable: `lr`. The tradeoff is that a lower LR may simply undertrain a recipe that is already stable at `2.0e-3`, but that is the cleanest first LR-localization question after the baseline repeat and is safer than opening the optimizer branch too early.",
research/history/logs/agent_action_0063.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With the `gated` mainline now stalled for ten rounds and `group_topk` already coming back slightly but clearly worse, the next highest-value matched architecture probe is `bucketed_topk`: it preserves the same fixed-`K` static weighted-sum decoder contract while changing only the selector architecture to a simple input-conditioned bucket specialization. This round answers one question only: under the matched `K=128`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EF=12` recipe, is `bucketed_topk` intrinsically strong enough to justify any later follow-up, or should it be ruled out immediately.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `bucketed_topk` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"bucketed_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 63 policy by changing exactly one primary variable: architecture. `bucketed_topk` is a cleaner probe than batch-coupled variants because it stays single-sample and export-compatible, and it is a cleaner runtime-aligned probe than heavier multi-stage or multi-branch families because it only asks whether light selector specialization helps enough to matter at all.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 63 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `bucketed_topk` after `group_topk` proved only roughly competitive and not mainline-worthy.","`bucketed_topk` remains directly compatible with LUTurbo export because the final reconstruction is still a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library with fixed `K`; the architecture change is confined to encoder-side bucket specialization before top-k selection.","Judge this probe strictly as a family-worthiness test against matched `gated` K128: if it is clearly worse, discard it and return to the `gated` mainline next round; if it is competitive, record the result but still return to the mainline per policy."],"next_hypotheses":["If `bucketed_topk` is clearly worse than matched `gated`, discard the family and return to the `gated` mainline next round.","If `bucketed_topk` is roughly competitive, record it as a possible selector-specialization direction but still return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy.","If `bucketed_topk` unexpectedly beats matched `gated`, schedule at most one later follow-up after the mandated return to the `gated` mainline."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
