research/history/logs/agent_action_0175.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"proxy","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` under the mainline recipe (`K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3e-3`). Final reconstruction is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j`, where the bucket gate only changes stage-1/2 selector scores and all decoded terms still come from static libraries `{U,V}`, codebook `C`, and residual dictionary `B`. This is `扩展兼容` with a clean LUTurbo export path, but the matched EF=2 selector is likely not worth continuing because bucketed dual scorers raise encoder selection cost to about `2.5x h×n`, so the policy should reject it before spending a long training run.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["Return to the mainline `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round and tune one cost knob at a time (`TRUNK_RANK`, `NUM_CODES`, or `STAGE1_RATIO`) to improve the feasible Pareto point without changing architecture.","If a future bucketed revisit is desired, only do it as a cost-reduction study on the bucketed family itself with primary variable `TRUNK_RANK` or `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM`, not as another matched-architecture probe."],"notes_to_memory":["`bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` is LUTurbo `扩展兼容`: bucket mixing changes selector-side scoring only; decode remains a finite weighted sum over static trunk/codebook/residual libraries.","At matched `K=128, EF=2`, the bucketed two-stage soft-codebook family estimates to about `selection_cost=2.5x` and is therefore over the `1.5x` hard budget; this makes it a likely fast policy-reject probe rather than a training candidate."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"Single-variable discipline is preserved: architecture is the only changed dimension, while `K/EF/optimizer/LR` are pinned to the mainline recipe. I am choosing an intentionally decisive probe: it is informative even if rejected, because the low-EF budget constraint is now the main gate and this family is known to be runtime-heavier. This does not claim the family is universally bad; it only answers whether it is worth continuing on the current feasible low-cost frontier.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` with the mainline recipe unchanged otherwise. The family is LUTurbo-exportable (`扩展兼容`) via a static trunk library plus static codebook and residual dictionaries, but its matched EF=2 selector cost is expected to exceed budget (`~2.5x h×n`), so the likely result is a cheap policy rejection that cleanly answers: this architecture is not worth continuing as a low-cost mainline candidate right now.","touched_files":[]}
