research/history/round_summaries/round_0094.json:19:    "hypothesis": "`lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` and `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` were the first recent matched probes to stay relatively close to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor, which suggests the coarse static codebook branch itself may be the useful part rather than the full two-stage residual path. The single highest-value matched architecture probe now is `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual`: it preserves LUTurbo-compatible static-library export while replacing the heavier residual selector with a simpler gate-modulated single-stage support path. This round asks one question only: under the exact matched `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe, is that cheaper codebook-plus-gated architecture competitive enough to deserve any future follow-up, or should it be ruled out as still clearly inferior to the current mainline?",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0094.json:23:    "family_name": "lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0094.json:24:    "family_stage": "prototype",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0094.json:25:    "self_review": "This is policy-clean: one probe, one primary variable, allowed `K`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` is explicit. I am choosing `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` over a heavier two-stage soft-codebook variant because the operator goal is LUTurbo online cost, not just SAE FVU, and this probe directly tests whether the promising soft-codebook branch survives with a deployment-friendlier selector. The main risk is that the added gate path may not beat the already-close grouped probe, but that still cleanly answers whether this family is worth continuing at all.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0094.json:52:      "Interpret this strictly as a family-worthiness test for a codebook-assisted single-stage gated selector that may lower LUTurbo online selection and compensation cost versus the mainline two-stage residual path.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0094.json:53:      "Return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome; do not chain additional new-family probes."
