research/history/round_summaries/round_0054.json:8:  "family_stage": "mainline",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0054.json:20:    "summary": "Stay on the active `gated` mainline and keep the family reference recipe fixed at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3` to complete the downward side of the LR localization around the current Hadamard anchor. Judge this run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if the lower LR yields a smoother mid/late descent and finishes below `0.142923`, then Hadamard shifted the preferred step size downward; if it is flatter or worse, lock `2.0e-3` as the operative mainline LR and stop the LR branch again.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0054.json:23:    "family_name": "gated",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0054.json:24:    "family_stage": "mainline",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0054.json:25:    "self_review": "This stays on the same family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `lr`, anchored on the current family reference point so it remains policy-clean. It also follows the requested mainline sequencing better than opening a new family or retuning K again: after the Hadamard-enabled anchor rejected the upward LR callback at `2.4e-3`, the most informative remaining single question is the symmetric downward callback before declaring the LR axis settled.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0054.json:84:      "If `LR=1.6e-3` is also worse or uniformly slower, close the LR branch and keep `LR=2.0e-3` as the shared mainline recipe before considering any further family-local recipe work."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0054.json:104:    "description": "Stay on the active `gated` mainline and keep the family reference recipe fixed at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3` to complete the downward side of the LR localization around the current Hadamard anchor. Judge this run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if the lower LR yields a smoother mid/late descent and finishes below `0.142923`, then Hadamard shifted the preferred step size downward; if it is flatter or worse, lock `2.0e-3` as the operative mainline LR and stop the LR branch again.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0054.json:105:    "self_review": "This stays on the same family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `lr`, anchored on the current family reference point so it remains policy-clean. It also follows the requested mainline sequencing better than opening a new family or retuning K again: after the Hadamard-enabled anchor rejected the upward LR callback at `2.4e-3`, the most informative remaining single question is the symmetric downward callback before declaring the LR axis settled.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0103.json:7:  "family_name": "lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0103.json:8:  "family_stage": "mainline",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0103.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Rounds 101 and 102 showed that the controller still treats `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual K=128 EXPANSION_FACTOR=12 OPTIMIZER=signum LR=2.0e-3` as the official mainline reference recipe for single-axis comparisons, so the cleanest next question is optimizer choice at that exact anchor. Switching only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam` while holding the reference `LR=2.0e-3` fixed tests whether this family has any optimizer headroom before spending another round on an optimizer-local LR callback, and it should be judged by the full curve shape against the signum reference rather than only the terminal FVU.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0103.json:23:    "family_name": "lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0103.json:24:    "family_stage": "mainline",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0103.json:25:    "self_review": "This corrects the last two policy rejects by anchoring the optimizer comparison to the controller-declared reference recipe instead of the unofficial `LR=2.4e-3` signum probe. Only one primary variable changes, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` remains explicit, and the result will cleanly answer whether `adam` deserves exactly one follow-up LR callback in this family.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0103.json:79:    "self_review": "This corrects the last two policy rejects by anchoring the optimizer comparison to the controller-declared reference recipe instead of the unofficial `LR=2.4e-3` signum probe. Only one primary variable changes, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` remains explicit, and the result will cleanly answer whether `adam` deserves exactly one follow-up LR callback in this family.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0064.json:7:  "family_name": "codebook_topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0064.json:8:  "family_stage": "prototype",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0064.json:19:    "hypothesis": "With the `gated` mainline stalled for eleven rounds and the lighter selector probes `group_topk` and `bucketed_topk` both coming back clearly worse, the next highest-value matched architecture probe is `codebook_topk`: it remains LUTurbo-compatible because the reconstruction is still a finite sum over static libraries, but it changes the architecture by adding a hard coarse codebook selection before the sparse residual. This round answers one question only: under the matched `K=128`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EF=12` recipe, is `codebook_topk` intrinsically strong enough to justify any later follow-up, or should it be ruled out immediately.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0064.json:23:    "family_name": "codebook_topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0064.json:24:    "family_stage": "prototype",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0064.json:52:      "`codebook_topk` is extended-compatible with LUTurbo because the final reconstruction can be exported as a hard-selected static coarse codebook vector plus a finite weighted sum over a static residual decoder library.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0064.json:53:      "Judge this probe strictly as a family-worthiness test against matched `gated` K128: if it is clearly worse, discard it and return to the `gated` mainline next round; if it is competitive, record the result but still return to the mainline per policy."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0064.json:56:      "If `codebook_topk` is clearly worse than matched `gated`, discard the family and return to the `gated` mainline next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0003.json:7:  "family_name": "topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0003.json:8:  "family_stage": "mainline",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0003.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Round 2 \u7684 6e-4 \u660e\u663e\u52a3\u4e8e 8e-4\uff0c\u8bf4\u660e\u5f53\u524d topk/signum \u4e3b\u7ebf\u66f4\u50cf\u662f\u6b20\u6b65\u957f\u800c\u4e0d\u662f\u8fc7\u51b2\uff1b\u672c\u8f6e\u53ea\u628a\u5b66\u4e60\u7387\u4e0a\u8c03\u5230 1e-3\uff0c\u68c0\u9a8c\u66f4\u79ef\u6781\u7684\u6b65\u957f\u662f\u5426\u80fd\u5728\u76f8\u540c family/optimizer/K \u4e0b\u5e26\u6765\u66f4\u5feb\u4e14\u4ecd\u7a33\u5b9a\u7684\u6536\u655b\uff0c\u5e76\u5237\u65b0 K=128 \u7684 FVU\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0003.json:20:    "summary": "\u7ee7\u7eed\u56f4\u7ed5 topk \u4e3b\u7ebf\u63a8\u8fdb\uff0c\u4e0d\u5f00\u65b0 family\uff0c\u4e0d\u6362\u4f18\u5316\u5668\uff0c\u4e0d\u52a8 K\u3002\u672c\u8f6e\u552f\u4e00\u4e3b\u53d8\u91cf\u4ecd\u662f LR\uff1a\u4ece\u53c2\u8003\u914d\u65b9 8e-4 \u4e0a\u8c03\u5230 1e-3\uff0c\u56de\u7b54\u201csignum+topk \u5728\u5f53\u524d\u8bbe\u7f6e\u4e0b\u662f\u5426\u66f4\u9700\u8981\u7a0d\u5927\u7684\u5b66\u4e60\u7387\u201d\u8fd9\u4e2a\u5355\u4e00\u95ee\u9898\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0003.json:23:    "family_name": "topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0003.json:24:    "family_stage": "mainline",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0003.json:106:    "description": "\u7ee7\u7eed\u56f4\u7ed5 topk \u4e3b\u7ebf\u63a8\u8fdb\uff0c\u4e0d\u5f00\u65b0 family\uff0c\u4e0d\u6362\u4f18\u5316\u5668\uff0c\u4e0d\u52a8 K\u3002\u672c\u8f6e\u552f\u4e00\u4e3b\u53d8\u91cf\u4ecd\u662f LR\uff1a\u4ece\u53c2\u8003\u914d\u65b9 8e-4 \u4e0a\u8c03\u5230 1e-3\uff0c\u56de\u7b54\u201csignum+topk \u5728\u5f53\u524d\u8bbe\u7f6e\u4e0b\u662f\u5426\u66f4\u9700\u8981\u7a0d\u5927\u7684\u5b66\u4e60\u7387\u201d\u8fd9\u4e2a\u5355\u4e00\u95ee\u9898\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0126.json:7:  "family_name": "lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0126.json:8:  "family_stage": "mainline",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0126.json:19:    "hypothesis": "最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j，其中 U(Vx) 对应可静态导出的 trunk 向量库，{c_m} 为静态 soft-codebook 库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，最终仍可落到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的‘查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿’推理链路，因此兼容性为扩展兼容。当前主线已确认 EF=2 在预算内，而 signum/LR/K 轴最近几轮没有带来改进，本轮只回答一个问题：在保持 family、K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变的前提下，下调 TRUNK_RANK 到 32，能否进一步压低 encoder 选择成本并维持可接受的 FVU，从而得到更优的 Pareto 权衡。",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0126.json:23:    "family_name": "lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0126.json:24:    "family_stage": "mainline",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0126.json:25:    "self_review": "本轮严格只改一个主变量，并把探索重心从已基本洗净的 signum/LR/K 轴转向更贴近 Pareto 目标的 selection-cost 轴。风险在于 TRUNK_RANK=32 可能过于激进，但它能最快回答该 family 是否还有内部压缩空间。",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0126.json:55:      "family 不变，兼容性仍为扩展兼容，导出路径不变：trunk 库 + soft-codebook 库 + residual 字典库。",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0126.json:83:    "self_review": "本轮严格只改一个主变量，并把探索重心从已基本洗净的 signum/LR/K 轴转向更贴近 Pareto 目标的 selection-cost 轴。风险在于 TRUNK_RANK=32 可能过于激进，但它能最快回答该 family 是否还有内部压缩空间。",
