research/history/round_summaries/round_0062.json:25:    "self_review": "This respects the Round 62 policy: one probe only, one main variable only, and the full mainline recipe stays matched except for architecture. `group_topk` is a better probe than heavier multi-branch variants because it is directly LUTurbo-compatible and has a plausible path to lower online selection cost rather than only improving training-side expressiveness.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0062.json:52:      "`group_topk` remains directly compatible with LUTurbo because reconstruction is still a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library; only the encoder-side selection rule changes.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0062.json:56:      "If `group_topk` is clearly worse than matched `gated` at `K=128`, discard the family and return to the `gated` mainline next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0062.json:78:    "self_review": "This respects the Round 62 policy: one probe only, one main variable only, and the full mainline recipe stays matched except for architecture. `group_topk` is a better probe than heavier multi-branch variants because it is directly LUTurbo-compatible and has a plausible path to lower online selection cost rather than only improving training-side expressiveness.",
