research/history/round_summaries/round_0203.json:55:      "\u82e5\u8fd0\u884c\u4ee3\u4ef7\u4e0a\u5347\u800c\u6536\u76ca\u5f88\u5c0f\uff0c\u5219\u628a\u56fa\u5b9a\u524d\u7f6e stage budget \u89c6\u4e3a\u8d1f\u9762\u4fe1\u53f7\uff0c\u4e0d\u7ee7\u7eed\u5728\u8be5 family \u4e0a\u5c55\u5f00 STAGE1_RATIO \u641c\u7d22\u3002"
research/history/round_summaries/round_0203.json:75:    "description": "\u6267\u884c\u4e00\u4e2a\u5408\u6cd5\u7684 matched architecture probe\uff1afamily_name \u5207\u5230 lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual\uff0c\u5176\u4f59 recipe \u4fdd\u6301 K=128\u3001EXPANSION_FACTOR=2\u3001OPTIMIZER=signum\u3001LR=3.0e-3 \u4e0d\u53d8\u3002\u8be5 family \u7684\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u4ecd\u53ef\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u9759\u6001\u67e5\u8868\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u4e3a\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\uff1b\u672c\u8f6e\u53ea\u56de\u7b54\u4e00\u4e2a\u95ee\u9898\uff0c\u5373\u56fa\u5b9a\u524d\u7f6e\u66f4\u591a stage1 \u7a00\u758f\u9884\u7b97\u7684 asymmetric two-stage \u7ed3\u6784\u5728\u5f53\u524d\u4f4e EF regime \u4e0b\u662f\u5426\u503c\u5f97\u7ee7\u7eed\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0203.json:76:    "self_review": "\u8fd9\u6b21\u6cbf\u7528 r202 \u5df2\u9a8c\u8bc1\u901a\u8fc7\u7684 architecture action \u5f62\u72b6\uff1aarchitecture \u53ea\u7531 family_name \u6307\u5b9a\uff0c\u4e0d\u5728 env_overrides \u4e2d\u91cd\u590d\u58f0\u660e\u3002\u76f8\u6bd4\u7ee7\u7eed\u91cd\u590d\u5df2\u5f97\u5230\u6709\u6548\u7ed3\u679c\u7684 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual \u6216 lowrank_residual\uff0c\u8fd9\u4e2a asymmetric two-stage \u53d8\u4f53\u662f\u5f53\u524d\u6700\u6709\u4fe1\u606f\u4ef7\u503c\u4e14\u5c1a\u672a\u83b7\u5f97\u6709\u6548 matched \u8fd0\u884c\u7684\u53ef\u884c family\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0087.json:7:  "family_name": "lowrank_gated_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0087.json:8:  "family_stage": "prototype",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0087.json:19:    "hypothesis": "With `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `lowrank_residual_vq`, and `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` all failing to challenge the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor, the highest-value remaining matched architecture probe is `lowrank_gated_residual`. It keeps the same low-rank trunk and static-library export contract, but replaces the two-stage residual path with a single gated residual selector that is materially simpler for LUTurbo online execution. If this simpler low-rank gated family is still clearly weaker under the exact matched `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe, then the current evidence favors keeping the two-stage residual structure rather than continuing single-stage low-rank selector variants.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0087.json:23:    "family_name": "lowrank_gated_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0087.json:24:    "family_stage": "prototype",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0087.json:25:    "self_review": "This follows the matched architecture probe rule by changing only `architecture` and keeping the mainline `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe fixed. `lowrank_gated_residual` is a cleaner LUTurbo-aligned probe than another multi-stage or codebook-heavy family because it preserves static exportability while potentially lowering online selection and compensation complexity. The risk is that earlier low-K history for this family was weak, so this round may mainly confirm that simpler single-stage low-rank gating cannot retain the mainline quality at K128.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0087.json:52:      "Judge this run strictly as a family-worthiness test for a simpler low-rank single-stage gated selector with potentially lower LUTurbo online cost; return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0087.json:76:    "self_review": "This follows the matched architecture probe rule by changing only `architecture` and keeping the mainline `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe fixed. `lowrank_gated_residual` is a cleaner LUTurbo-aligned probe than another multi-stage or codebook-heavy family because it preserves static exportability while potentially lowering online selection and compensation complexity. The risk is that earlier low-K history for this family was weak, so this round may mainly confirm that simpler single-stage low-rank gating cannot retain the mainline quality at K128.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0035.json:7:  "family_name": "gated",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0035.json:8:  "family_stage": "mainline",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0035.json:20:    "summary": "Round 34 answered the loss-side probe: a small aux term did not improve on the plain `gated` anchor and should be treated as non-helpful for now. Following the requested order, the next single-variable probe is preprocessing. Keep family, K, EF, optimizer, and LR fixed, enable Hadamard rotation with default settings, and judge the result by curve shape as much as terminal FVU. If the run descends more steadily and finishes below `0.149866`, preprocessing is a real lever for `gated`; if it is flat, noisy, or only ties within noise, preserve the plain anchor and avoid further preprocess branching.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0035.json:23:    "family_name": "gated",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0035.json:24:    "family_stage": "mainline",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0035.json:25:    "self_review": "This stays on the same family, keeps EF fixed at 12, does not touch K, and changes exactly one main variable: preprocessing via `use_hadamard`. It also follows the prescribed sequence by moving to preprocess only after the LR, optimizer, and loss-side probes failed to improve the anchored gated recipe.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0035.json:80:    "description": "Round 34 answered the loss-side probe: a small aux term did not improve on the plain `gated` anchor and should be treated as non-helpful for now. Following the requested order, the next single-variable probe is preprocessing. Keep family, K, EF, optimizer, and LR fixed, enable Hadamard rotation with default settings, and judge the result by curve shape as much as terminal FVU. If the run descends more steadily and finishes below `0.149866`, preprocessing is a real lever for `gated`; if it is flat, noisy, or only ties within noise, preserve the plain anchor and avoid further preprocess branching.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0035.json:81:    "self_review": "This stays on the same family, keeps EF fixed at 12, does not touch K, and changes exactly one main variable: preprocessing via `use_hadamard`. It also follows the prescribed sequence by moving to preprocess only after the LR, optimizer, and loss-side probes failed to improve the anchored gated recipe.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:7:  "family_name": "gated",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:8:  "family_stage": "prototype",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Round 28 showed that `whitened_topk` is not worth continuing: under a matched probe it failed catastrophically, so the next and only remaining useful question in this probe slot is whether a different directly compatible support-selection variant has any architectural merit at all. `gated` preserves the same static-dictionary weighted-sum reconstruction form as `topk` while changing only how support is selected and scaled, so this round asks a single yes/no question: is `gated` competitive enough under a matched K128/signum/LR=1.6e-3/EF12 probe to justify any future follow-up.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:20:    "summary": "Run one matched architecture probe on `gated`. Keep `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and the current stabilized runtime/aux recipe fixed, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `topk` to `gated` to test whether this directly export-compatible family is worth continuing.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:23:    "family_name": "gated",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:24:    "family_stage": "prototype",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:25:    "self_review": "This obeys the matched-probe rule by changing only the architecture axis, keeps the core mainline recipe fixed, and selects a family that remains compatible with LUTurbo's static-vector weighted-sum deployment contract. The main risk is that the extra gating branch may add training complexity without improving quality or runtime-aligned sparsity behavior, but that is exactly the family-worthiness question this probe is intended to answer before returning to the topk mainline.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:80:      "`gated` remains directly compatible with LUTurbo deployment because the final reconstruction is still a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library with fixed `K`; the change is confined to encoder-side gating and support scoring.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:81:      "Judge this round as a pure family-worthiness probe against the stabilized K128 topk control: if it is clearly worse or unstable, archive it and return to topk next round; if it is competitive, record that but still return to the mainline per policy."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:85:      "If `gated` is competitive but not clearly better, record it as a plausible alternative family and still return to the topk mainline next round.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:105:    "description": "Run one matched architecture probe on `gated`. Keep `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and the current stabilized runtime/aux recipe fixed, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `topk` to `gated` to test whether this directly export-compatible family is worth continuing.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0029.json:106:    "self_review": "This obeys the matched-probe rule by changing only the architecture axis, keeps the core mainline recipe fixed, and selects a family that remains compatible with LUTurbo's static-vector weighted-sum deployment contract. The main risk is that the extra gating branch may add training complexity without improving quality or runtime-aligned sparsity behavior, but that is exactly the family-worthiness question this probe is intended to answer before returning to the topk mainline.",
