research/history/round_summaries/round_0078.json:19:    "hypothesis": "`two_stage_residual` has stalled at the matched `K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=2.0e-3` anchor after several clean recipe checks and three weaker simple-family probes. A single matched probe on `lowrank_two_stage_residual` is the highest-value architecture question now: it preserves the same staged static-library decomposition contract while adding a stronger coarse low-rank trunk. If it cannot beat or clearly pressure the current `two_stage_residual` anchor under the exact same recipe, then the added coarse-path complexity is not worth continuing in this regime.",
