research/history/round_summaries/round_0078.json:25:    "self_review": "This is policy-clean: one matched architecture probe, one primary variable, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` is explicitly pinned. The main tradeoff is that `lowrank_two_stage_residual` likely raises online coefficient cost versus the current mainline, so it is only worth continuing if the FVU gain is material rather than marginal. I am choosing it over another simple selector family because recent matched probes already showed that lighter alternatives are clearly behind the current anchor.",
