research/history/round_summaries/round_0111.json:19:    "hypothesis": "After five consecutive non-improving mainline rounds, the single highest-value matched architecture probe is the nearest strong alternative family `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`. It preserves the same LUTurbo-compatible static export form as the current `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline, but changes only the stage allocation structure. Holding `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed isolates one clean question: does the asymmetric two-stage variant remain competitive enough on the matched reference recipe to deserve future follow-up, or should focus stay on the simpler current mainline family.",
