research/history/round_summaries/round_0164.json:23:    "self_review": "Upside is bounded because this family only changes a fixed stage split and was not strong historically at higher-EF regimes, so a null result is plausible. Still, it is the cleanest policy-safe matched probe that isolates architecture without confounding cost increases.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0164.json:39:      "If it is competitive at similar runtime, the next single-variable follow-up is STAGE1_RATIO tuning within this asymmetric family rather than opening another new architecture family."
