research/history/round_summaries/round_0020.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Round 19 showed that `topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/EF=12` at `K=8` suffered a large quality drop and much heavier dead-feature pressure, with the late curve nearly flattening but not fully collapsing. This round changes only `K`, moving from `8` to `4`, to answer the single remaining boundary question: whether the current export-compatible topk recipe has any usable signal left at the absolute minimum allowed K, or whether `K=8` already marks the effective floor.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0020.json:23:    "family_name": "topk",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0020.json:24:    "family_stage": "mainline",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0020.json:25:    "self_review": "This stays on the active `topk` family, changes exactly one primary variable (`k`), respects the fixed `EF=12` rule and allowed-K set, and closes the current K-only frontier scan cleanly. The main risk is that `K=4` may be clearly past the useful regime, but `command=\"stop\"` is disallowed and this is the most informative remaining single-variable question because it determines whether `K=8` is merely weak or already beyond the practical floor.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0020.json:56:      "If `K=4` collapses or adds very little usable signal, treat `K=8` or `K=16` as the practical floor and return to non-K recipe tuning on the same family.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0020.json:79:    "self_review": "This stays on the active `topk` family, changes exactly one primary variable (`k`), respects the fixed `EF=12` rule and allowed-K set, and closes the current K-only frontier scan cleanly. The main risk is that `K=4` may be clearly past the useful regime, but `command=\"stop\"` is disallowed and this is the most informative remaining single-variable question because it determines whether `K=8` is merely weak or already beyond the practical floor.",
