research/history/round_summaries/round_0098.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Round 97 showed that lowering `LR` to `1.6e-3` on the confirmed `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` K128 baseline was slightly worse, so the next single mainline question is the symmetric upward signum LR probe. Raising `LR` to `2.4e-3` tests whether this family benefits from a bit more step size for faster early and mid descent without destabilizing late training; the result should be judged from the whole curve against the archived `2.0e-3` and `1.6e-3` runs, not just the terminal FVU.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0098.json:23:    "family_name": "lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual",
