research/history/round_summaries/round_0098.json:25:    "self_review": "This follows the required LR-localization sequence: same family, same `K`, same optimizer, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` pinned, and exactly one primary variable changes. The main risk is overshooting a recipe that may already be near its best at `2.0e-3`, but this is the clean remaining LR question before it is defensible to close the signum LR branch and move to optimizer.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0098.json:53:      "Only after this LR bracket is resolved should the optimizer branch open on this family."
