research/history/round_summaries/round_0024.json:25:    "self_review": "This stays on the active `topk` family, changes only one non-core variable on the exact reference backbone, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and follows directly from the evidence that both weaker and stronger `AUXK_ALPHA` failed to beat the baseline. The main risk is that the threshold change may have little effect over this training horizon, but it is the cleanest remaining single-variable way to probe whether the auxiliary mechanism is mis-timed rather than mis-scaled.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0024.json:87:    "self_review": "This stays on the active `topk` family, changes only one non-core variable on the exact reference backbone, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and follows directly from the evidence that both weaker and stronger `AUXK_ALPHA` failed to beat the baseline. The main risk is that the threshold change may have little effect over this training horizon, but it is the cleanest remaining single-variable way to probe whether the auxiliary mechanism is mis-timed rather than mis-scaled.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0099.json:7:  "family_name": "lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0099.json:8:  "family_stage": "mainline",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0099.json:21:    "family_name": "lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0099.json:22:    "family_stage": "mainline",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0099.json:23:    "self_review": "This stays within the same family, keeps `K` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and changes no new axis beyond confirming the only signum LR setting that has actually improved the endpoint so far. The tradeoff is spending one round on confirmation instead of opening the optimizer branch immediately, but that is justified because the mainline anchor should be localized on a reproducible LR before optimizer comparisons are made.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0099.json:51:      "Only after confirming whether `LR=2.4e-3` is a stable anchor should the optimizer branch open on this family."
