research/history/round_summaries/round_0039.json:25:    "self_review": "This stays on the active family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and changes exactly one core variable: `lr`. It also follows the prescribed order now that the clean baseline has been backfilled successfully. The main risk is that `2.0e-3` could overdrive training, but the evidence so far points the other way: `1.2e-3` was clearly slower/worse, and the refreshed `1.6e-3` baseline was still improving late.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0039.json:105:    "self_review": "This stays on the active family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and changes exactly one core variable: `lr`. It also follows the prescribed order now that the clean baseline has been backfilled successfully. The main risk is that `2.0e-3` could overdrive training, but the evidence so far points the other way: `1.2e-3` was clearly slower/worse, and the refreshed `1.6e-3` baseline was still improving late.",
