research/history/round_summaries/round_0105.json:25:    "self_review": "This follows the required mainline sequence after a fresh architecture win: keep the new family, hold `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, optimizer, and LR fixed, and spend one round confirming that the improved result is repeatable before probing learning rate or optimizer. The tradeoff is delaying tuning by one round, but that is justified because recipe comparisons are only meaningful once the new baseline is shown to be stable.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0105.json:56:      "If the baseline repeat matches or nearly matches Round 104 on curve shape and endpoint, open the within-family LR branch next, starting with one symmetric learning-rate probe.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0105.json:79:    "self_review": "This follows the required mainline sequence after a fresh architecture win: keep the new family, hold `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, optimizer, and LR fixed, and spend one round confirming that the improved result is repeatable before probing learning rate or optimizer. The tradeoff is delaying tuning by one round, but that is justified because recipe comparisons are only meaningful once the new baseline is shown to be stable.",
