research/history/round_summaries/round_0070.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Rounds 65 and 66 established a clean, reproducible `two_stage_residual` mainline baseline at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`. The next single mainline question, in the prescribed order, is the first within-family learning-rate probe: does lowering `LR` to `1.6e-3` improve the late-stage curve or final FVU for `two_stage_residual`, or is the archived `2.0e-3` recipe already the better operating point?",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0070.json:23:    "family_name": "two_stage_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0070.json:24:    "family_stage": "mainline",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0070.json:25:    "self_review": "This keeps the search on the active mainline family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, uses an allowed `K`, and changes exactly one primary variable: `lr`. It also directly fixes the recent policy-reject cause by using `primary_variable=\"lr\"` rather than `learning_rate`. The main risk is that the baseline may already be near-optimal and `1.6e-3` may simply converge more slowly, but that is the highest-value single question before opening the optimizer branch.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0070.json:76:      "Keep the comparison anchored to the archived `two_stage_residual` baseline at `K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and read the whole curve, not just the endpoint, to determine whether the family wants a slightly smaller step size."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0070.json:102:    "self_review": "This keeps the search on the active mainline family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, uses an allowed `K`, and changes exactly one primary variable: `lr`. It also directly fixes the recent policy-reject cause by using `primary_variable=\"lr\"` rather than `learning_rate`. The main risk is that the baseline may already be near-optimal and `1.6e-3` may simply converge more slowly, but that is the highest-value single question before opening the optimizer branch.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0168.json:7:  "family_name": "lowrank_gated_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0168.json:8:  "family_stage": "prototype",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0168.json:20:    "summary": "Run one valid matched architecture probe on `lowrank_gated_residual` while keeping the `K=128`, `EF=2`, `signum`, `LR=3.0e-3` mainline recipe fixed. This cleanly tests whether a cheaper single-stage low-rank gated architecture is worth any continued attention under LUTurbo-compatible low-EF constraints.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0168.json:23:    "family_name": "lowrank_gated_residual",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0168.json:24:    "family_stage": "prototype",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0168.json:53:      "Judge family worthiness using `tokens_per_sec`, total duration, and `final_total_tokens` alongside final FVU, because a tiny quality gain with noticeably worse runtime would be negative for LUTurbo\u2019s true objective."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0168.json:57:      "If it is modestly worse in FVU but materially better in throughput or total runtime, record it as a lower-cost compatible side branch, but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0168.json:58:      "If it is unexpectedly close to the mainline at lower selection cost, schedule at most one later family-specific follow-up after the required return to the mainline."
research/history/round_summaries/round_0168.json:78:    "description": "Run one valid matched architecture probe on `lowrank_gated_residual` while keeping the `K=128`, `EF=2`, `signum`, `LR=3.0e-3` mainline recipe fixed. This cleanly tests whether a cheaper single-stage low-rank gated architecture is worth any continued attention under LUTurbo-compatible low-EF constraints.",
